WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:18.218 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:00:18.218 --> 00:00:19.786 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA GARR: Hi, I'm Lisa Garr.

00:00:19.786 --> 00:00:21.655 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to "Gaiam Inspirations."

00:00:21.655 --> 00:00:23.857 align:middle line:84%
We are coming to you live
from the Gaiam studios

00:00:23.857 --> 00:00:25.459 align:middle line:90%
here in Boulder, Colorado.

00:00:25.459 --> 00:00:27.794 align:middle line:84%
And since this is a
live, interactive show,

00:00:27.794 --> 00:00:29.363 align:middle line:84%
I encourage you to
communicate with us

00:00:29.363 --> 00:00:31.031 align:middle line:90%
via Facebook and Twitter.

00:00:31.031 --> 00:00:33.066 align:middle line:84%
Keep the conversation
going and the communication

00:00:33.066 --> 00:00:33.800 align:middle line:90%
going throughout the show.

00:00:33.800 --> 00:00:35.135 align:middle line:84%
Many of you already
have done that.

00:00:35.135 --> 00:00:36.136 align:middle line:90%
So thank you very much.

00:00:36.136 --> 00:00:38.505 align:middle line:84%
We'll get to your comments
later on in the show.

00:00:38.505 --> 00:00:40.941 align:middle line:84%
So let me ask you, for
those people who have ever

00:00:40.941 --> 00:00:43.377 align:middle line:84%
had a dream about
an event happening

00:00:43.377 --> 00:00:46.847 align:middle line:84%
and then it actually occurs,
listen very carefully.

00:00:46.847 --> 00:00:49.816 align:middle line:84%
For those of you who have
ever had a coincidence where

00:00:49.816 --> 00:00:52.352 align:middle line:84%
you've thought of someone and
then they call, or you thought

00:00:52.352 --> 00:00:54.621 align:middle line:84%
of an event and it
actually happens,

00:00:54.621 --> 00:00:57.291 align:middle line:84%
then it may not
be a coincidence.

00:00:57.291 --> 00:00:59.226 align:middle line:90%
It may be a premonition.

00:00:59.226 --> 00:01:02.062 align:middle line:84%
And there is science
behind this concept.

00:01:02.062 --> 00:01:04.364 align:middle line:90%
Joining me is Dr. Larry Dossey.

00:01:04.364 --> 00:01:06.233 align:middle line:84%
He is responsible
for changing the way

00:01:06.233 --> 00:01:08.735 align:middle line:84%
that the medical
profession relates

00:01:08.735 --> 00:01:12.839 align:middle line:84%
to the concept of prayer,
and the scientific validation

00:01:12.839 --> 00:01:14.741 align:middle line:84%
of prayer, in the
medical profession.

00:01:14.741 --> 00:01:16.944 align:middle line:84%
He is joining me today to
talk about the cutting edge

00:01:16.944 --> 00:01:19.246 align:middle line:84%
science behind his
latest book, called

00:01:19.246 --> 00:01:21.315 align:middle line:90%
The Power of Premonitions.

00:01:21.315 --> 00:01:22.149 align:middle line:90%
Welcome to the show.

00:01:22.149 --> 00:01:23.383 align:middle line:90%
Thanks for being here.

00:01:23.383 --> 00:01:24.418 align:middle line:84%
>>LARRY DOSSEY:
Wouldn't miss it.

00:01:24.418 --> 00:01:24.851 align:middle line:90%
Thanks.

00:01:24.851 --> 00:01:25.485 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I know.

00:01:25.485 --> 00:01:27.621 align:middle line:84%
So what you have done
with-- first of all,

00:01:27.621 --> 00:01:29.890 align:middle line:84%
you're a doctor of
internal medicine.

00:01:29.890 --> 00:01:33.327 align:middle line:84%
And you started writing
about healing and prayer

00:01:33.327 --> 00:01:34.261 align:middle line:90%
20 years ago.

00:01:34.261 --> 00:01:36.596 align:middle line:84%
This book is in
its 20th year now.

00:01:36.596 --> 00:01:39.866 align:middle line:84%
How did the medical profession
receive that information

00:01:39.866 --> 00:01:40.567 align:middle line:90%
from you?

00:01:40.567 --> 00:01:42.502 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I think
it was sort of a shock

00:01:42.502 --> 00:01:47.774 align:middle line:84%
to them to begin with, but
they got over it very quickly.

00:01:47.774 --> 00:01:50.944 align:middle line:84%
The reason, Lisa, is
that it became obvious,

00:01:50.944 --> 00:01:53.213 align:middle line:84%
from the information
in the book,

00:01:53.213 --> 00:01:56.984 align:middle line:84%
that, as you've already said,
there really is science here.

00:01:56.984 --> 00:01:58.485 align:middle line:84%
I think a lot of
people thought we

00:01:58.485 --> 00:02:00.654 align:middle line:84%
were trying to sell
religion with the book.

00:02:00.654 --> 00:02:03.357 align:middle line:84%
And when they discovered
that wasn't the case,

00:02:03.357 --> 00:02:05.559 align:middle line:84%
we were just trying
to do good science,

00:02:05.559 --> 00:02:07.394 align:middle line:84%
then interesting things
started happening.

00:02:07.394 --> 00:02:09.162 align:middle line:84%
People started
doing more research.

00:02:09.162 --> 00:02:11.064 align:middle line:84%
The medical schools
came on board

00:02:11.064 --> 00:02:14.134 align:middle line:84%
and started emphasizing the
connection between spirituality

00:02:14.134 --> 00:02:14.634 align:middle line:90%
and health.

00:02:14.634 --> 00:02:17.170 align:middle line:84%
And then we were off
to the races, really.

00:02:17.170 --> 00:02:19.973 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Dr Dossey's
book is in many,

00:02:19.973 --> 00:02:21.141 align:middle line:90%
many of the medical schools.

00:02:21.141 --> 00:02:23.844 align:middle line:84%
As a matter of fact, out
of the 128 medical schools,

00:02:23.844 --> 00:02:28.081 align:middle line:84%
there's-- how many teach
alternative healing, actually?

00:02:28.081 --> 00:02:29.583 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Actually,
about 90 of them

00:02:29.583 --> 00:02:31.752 align:middle line:84%
have formal places
in the curriculum

00:02:31.752 --> 00:02:33.387 align:middle line:90%
for this sort of information.

00:02:33.387 --> 00:02:33.887 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:02:33.887 --> 00:02:35.489 align:middle line:84%
>>LARRY DOSSEY: This
is a real change.

00:02:35.489 --> 00:02:37.524 align:middle line:84%
Because back when
the book was written,

00:02:37.524 --> 00:02:40.327 align:middle line:84%
in 1993, only three
medical schools

00:02:40.327 --> 00:02:42.362 align:middle line:90%
would even touch this topic.

00:02:42.362 --> 00:02:45.732 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And then you come out
with a book on premonitions.

00:02:45.732 --> 00:02:48.135 align:middle line:84%
How did you get
started on that topic?

00:02:48.135 --> 00:02:51.371 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I had a few
of those suckers myself.

00:02:51.371 --> 00:02:54.574 align:middle line:84%
Actually, the first year I
was in medical school-- excuse

00:02:54.574 --> 00:02:58.211 align:middle line:84%
me, the first year I was
in medical practice--

00:02:58.211 --> 00:03:02.182 align:middle line:84%
I had a series of what are
called precognitive dreams.

00:03:02.182 --> 00:03:05.719 align:middle line:84%
And some of them were so
camera-like in detail about

00:03:05.719 --> 00:03:07.954 align:middle line:84%
what would happen
the next day, I

00:03:07.954 --> 00:03:11.091 align:middle line:84%
was just really
actually unnerved.

00:03:11.091 --> 00:03:13.093 align:middle line:84%
The reason I was
is because I'd been

00:03:13.093 --> 00:03:14.428 align:middle line:90%
taught that this doesn't happen.

00:03:14.428 --> 00:03:16.797 align:middle line:84%
The world does not
behave like that.

00:03:16.797 --> 00:03:18.832 align:middle line:84%
You can't know something
before it happens.

00:03:18.832 --> 00:03:20.267 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How did
you know it wasn't

00:03:20.267 --> 00:03:23.904 align:middle line:84%
an accident or
just foreshadowing?

00:03:23.904 --> 00:03:26.406 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Because
of several reasons.

00:03:26.406 --> 00:03:29.776 align:middle line:84%
For one thing, the dream
was so odd and complex

00:03:29.776 --> 00:03:33.579 align:middle line:84%
and detailed I couldn't have
made it up if I had tried.

00:03:33.579 --> 00:03:39.286 align:middle line:84%
And then, when it came true
the next day in exotic detail--

00:03:39.286 --> 00:03:40.754 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: You have
to tell the story.

00:03:40.754 --> 00:03:42.856 align:middle line:90%
I yeah-- I need to know.

00:03:42.856 --> 00:03:45.425 align:middle line:90%
What happened?

00:03:45.425 --> 00:03:48.795 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I dreamt
a series of events

00:03:48.795 --> 00:03:51.098 align:middle line:84%
that had to do with the
three-year-old son of one

00:03:51.098 --> 00:03:57.304 align:middle line:84%
of my colleagues at the
Dallas Diagnostic Association.

00:03:57.304 --> 00:04:01.842 align:middle line:84%
I dreamt that this young man
had a medical test the next day.

00:04:01.842 --> 00:04:06.246 align:middle line:84%
He was lying on a
sterile-looking examination

00:04:06.246 --> 00:04:07.247 align:middle line:90%
table.

00:04:07.247 --> 00:04:10.350 align:middle line:84%
A technician at the
head of the table

00:04:10.350 --> 00:04:12.185 align:middle line:84%
was trying to do
some sort of test.

00:04:12.185 --> 00:04:13.820 align:middle line:90%
It looked like an EEG.

00:04:13.820 --> 00:04:17.124 align:middle line:84%
She had things she was trying
to paste onto his skull,

00:04:17.124 --> 00:04:18.158 align:middle line:90%
and so on.

00:04:18.158 --> 00:04:21.228 align:middle line:84%
The mother was standing
by the side of the kid,

00:04:21.228 --> 00:04:25.098 align:middle line:84%
trying to lend comfort, because
this kid wasn't buying it.

00:04:25.098 --> 00:04:27.734 align:middle line:84%
He just went berserk--
crying, screaming, kicking.

00:04:27.734 --> 00:04:29.136 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: This was
all in the dream?

00:04:29.136 --> 00:04:30.871 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: This was
all in the dream.

00:04:30.871 --> 00:04:33.406 align:middle line:84%
And finally, the
technician just got fed up.

00:04:33.406 --> 00:04:34.407 align:middle line:90%
And she said, I quit.

00:04:34.407 --> 00:04:36.076 align:middle line:90%
She turns around and walks away.

00:04:36.076 --> 00:04:37.644 align:middle line:84%
And I thought, this
is a crazy dream.

00:04:37.644 --> 00:04:38.612 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Did you ever
think, why are you

00:04:38.612 --> 00:04:40.013 align:middle line:90%
dreaming about this boy?

00:04:40.013 --> 00:04:43.984 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Yes, I woke up and
I actually had the sensation

00:04:43.984 --> 00:04:47.020 align:middle line:84%
that, gee, this feels like
the most vivid dream I've ever

00:04:47.020 --> 00:04:47.854 align:middle line:90%
had in my life.

00:04:47.854 --> 00:04:49.789 align:middle line:84%
Which didn't make
any sense, either.

00:04:49.789 --> 00:04:51.057 align:middle line:90%
So I go to work the next day.

00:04:51.057 --> 00:04:54.427 align:middle line:84%
I make hospital rounds,
seeing patients in the office.

00:04:54.427 --> 00:04:59.799 align:middle line:84%
And at lunch, I'm sitting with
the boy's father, my colleague.

00:04:59.799 --> 00:05:00.901 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Your colleague, OK.

00:05:00.901 --> 00:05:04.004 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: In walks his wife,
holding this little boy

00:05:04.004 --> 00:05:04.638 align:middle line:90%
in her arms.

00:05:04.638 --> 00:05:05.972 align:middle line:90%
His head is wet.

00:05:05.972 --> 00:05:07.274 align:middle line:90%
He's crying.

00:05:07.274 --> 00:05:09.142 align:middle line:90%
And he's very upset.

00:05:09.142 --> 00:05:13.079 align:middle line:84%
So she tells her
husband my dream,

00:05:13.079 --> 00:05:16.283 align:middle line:84%
how they'd just come
from the EEG laboratory.

00:05:16.283 --> 00:05:17.984 align:middle line:90%
They tried to do the test.

00:05:17.984 --> 00:05:20.687 align:middle line:84%
The technician, although
she was famous for being

00:05:20.687 --> 00:05:23.924 align:middle line:84%
able to do these
tests on children,

00:05:23.924 --> 00:05:26.526 align:middle line:84%
nonetheless she just got fed
up with it and she just said,

00:05:26.526 --> 00:05:27.928 align:middle line:90%
I can't do this anymore.

00:05:27.928 --> 00:05:28.929 align:middle line:90%
She quits.

00:05:28.929 --> 00:05:31.097 align:middle line:84%
The mother's standing
there by the side.

00:05:31.097 --> 00:05:34.734 align:middle line:84%
Now, a skeptic would say,
well it was just coincidence.

00:05:34.734 --> 00:05:36.069 align:middle line:90%
I can't buy it.

00:05:36.069 --> 00:05:38.305 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Did you ever figure
out why you had the dream?

00:05:38.305 --> 00:05:39.472 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: No, not at all.

00:05:39.472 --> 00:05:40.640 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: No, you just had it.

00:05:40.640 --> 00:05:42.008 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Yes, and--

00:05:42.008 --> 00:05:44.144 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: There was no
significant meaning behind it.

00:05:44.144 --> 00:05:46.546 align:middle line:84%
And so what happened
when you shared that?

00:05:46.546 --> 00:05:48.648 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: When the wife
left with the little boy,

00:05:48.648 --> 00:05:51.183 align:middle line:84%
I turned to my colleague
and I said, could I

00:05:51.183 --> 00:05:53.086 align:middle line:90%
have known what just happened?

00:05:53.086 --> 00:05:56.056 align:middle line:84%
And he looked at me
like, of course not.

00:05:56.056 --> 00:05:57.057 align:middle line:90%
That's silly.

00:05:57.057 --> 00:06:00.093 align:middle line:90%
Then I revealed to him my dream.

00:06:00.093 --> 00:06:02.362 align:middle line:90%
He was disturbed by that.

00:06:02.362 --> 00:06:04.598 align:middle line:84%
He, like I, knew that
this couldn't happen.

00:06:04.598 --> 00:06:05.765 align:middle line:90%
But there it was.

00:06:05.765 --> 00:06:07.467 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So what led
you into eventually

00:06:07.467 --> 00:06:08.735 align:middle line:90%
writing a book about it?

00:06:08.735 --> 00:06:10.804 align:middle line:84%
That was the beginning
for you, right?

00:06:10.804 --> 00:06:12.072 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Well, several things.

00:06:12.072 --> 00:06:15.175 align:middle line:84%
For one thing, I found that I
could not avoid premonitions.

00:06:15.175 --> 00:06:18.411 align:middle line:84%
My patients began to
come to me telling me

00:06:18.411 --> 00:06:21.848 align:middle line:84%
their dreams, which
would prove to be true.

00:06:21.848 --> 00:06:24.818 align:middle line:84%
Nurses discovered that I
had an interest in this

00:06:24.818 --> 00:06:28.388 align:middle line:84%
and flooded me with
their premonitions.

00:06:28.388 --> 00:06:31.191 align:middle line:84%
And eventually, doctors began
to tell me their experiences,

00:06:31.191 --> 00:06:32.492 align:middle line:90%
also.

00:06:32.492 --> 00:06:34.594 align:middle line:84%
So I tried to hide from
them, but I couldn't.

00:06:34.594 --> 00:06:36.329 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It was like
when you allowed that

00:06:36.329 --> 00:06:39.399 align:middle line:84%
into your consciousness,
it started to attract.

00:06:39.399 --> 00:06:41.134 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: That's a
great way to put it.

00:06:41.134 --> 00:06:42.836 align:middle line:84%
But there was another
crucial development

00:06:42.836 --> 00:06:46.406 align:middle line:84%
which was pivotal
in writing the book.

00:06:46.406 --> 00:06:51.244 align:middle line:84%
A few years ago, very talented
investigators-- scientists--

00:06:51.244 --> 00:06:54.714 align:middle line:84%
began to do experiments
determining whether or not

00:06:54.714 --> 00:06:56.783 align:middle line:90%
people could sense the future.

00:06:56.783 --> 00:06:59.986 align:middle line:84%
These were called
presentiment studies.

00:06:59.986 --> 00:07:01.955 align:middle line:90%
They're computer-based studies.

00:07:01.955 --> 00:07:04.190 align:middle line:84%
Dr. Dean Radin is
one of the people

00:07:04.190 --> 00:07:05.825 align:middle line:90%
who pioneered that field.

00:07:05.825 --> 00:07:09.396 align:middle line:84%
And beyond any question,
any shadow of doubt,

00:07:09.396 --> 00:07:11.898 align:middle line:84%
he and others proved
that people can

00:07:11.898 --> 00:07:14.034 align:middle line:84%
sense what's coming
up into the future.

00:07:14.034 --> 00:07:16.269 align:middle line:84%
You can't fool these
computer-based experiments.

00:07:16.269 --> 00:07:17.637 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How do
you do those types

00:07:17.637 --> 00:07:18.972 align:middle line:90%
of experiments computer based?

00:07:18.972 --> 00:07:20.674 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, it's
quite interesting.

00:07:20.674 --> 00:07:23.209 align:middle line:84%
What you do is you get hooked
up to have something measured

00:07:23.209 --> 00:07:24.778 align:middle line:84%
in your body, like
your blood pressure

00:07:24.778 --> 00:07:29.949 align:middle line:84%
or pulse rate-- something of
that sort, one of the stress

00:07:29.949 --> 00:07:31.751 align:middle line:90%
measures in the body.

00:07:31.751 --> 00:07:35.488 align:middle line:84%
And so the computer is
going to show you an image.

00:07:35.488 --> 00:07:37.590 align:middle line:84%
And it's going to
be one of two types.

00:07:37.590 --> 00:07:39.392 align:middle line:84%
It's going to be
a horrible image,

00:07:39.392 --> 00:07:42.862 align:middle line:84%
like an autopsy or a grisly
car wreck, something like this.

00:07:42.862 --> 00:07:45.632 align:middle line:84%
Or it's going to be a
peaceful, serene image,

00:07:45.632 --> 00:07:49.202 align:middle line:84%
like a scene at the beach or in
nature, something of that sort.

00:07:49.202 --> 00:07:51.404 align:middle line:84%
You don't know which
it's going to be.

00:07:51.404 --> 00:07:53.573 align:middle line:84%
The computer doesn't
know, because the computer

00:07:53.573 --> 00:07:56.643 align:middle line:84%
is going to make a
random choice about what

00:07:56.643 --> 00:07:57.744 align:middle line:90%
it's going to show you.

00:07:57.744 --> 00:07:59.546 align:middle line:90%
Now, here's what happens.

00:07:59.546 --> 00:08:02.082 align:middle line:84%
If the image that the
computer's going to show you

00:08:02.082 --> 00:08:05.885 align:middle line:84%
is one of these awful,
disturbing images,

00:08:05.885 --> 00:08:09.556 align:middle line:84%
before it even shows it
to you, before it even

00:08:09.556 --> 00:08:12.025 align:middle line:84%
selects the image,
your body begins

00:08:12.025 --> 00:08:15.929 align:middle line:84%
to generate an exaggerated
stress response.

00:08:15.929 --> 00:08:17.130 align:middle line:90%
Your blood pressure goes up.

00:08:17.130 --> 00:08:18.131 align:middle line:90%
Your heart rate goes up.

00:08:18.131 --> 00:08:21.234 align:middle line:84%
Your pupils dilate--
before you even

00:08:21.234 --> 00:08:23.636 align:middle line:84%
know what the image
is going to be.

00:08:23.636 --> 00:08:25.839 align:middle line:84%
Before you're even
exposed to it.

00:08:25.839 --> 00:08:27.741 align:middle line:84%
This doesn't happen
to the same degree

00:08:27.741 --> 00:08:30.377 align:middle line:84%
if the image is going to be
one of those peaceful things.

00:08:30.377 --> 00:08:35.148 align:middle line:84%
So the question is, how
in the world do you know--

00:08:35.148 --> 00:08:36.515 align:middle line:90%
how does your body know--

00:08:36.515 --> 00:08:37.150 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: How does it know?

00:08:37.150 --> 00:08:38.618 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: --what's going
to happen in the future?

00:08:38.618 --> 00:08:40.653 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: But the fact that it
does know-- we don't know how--

00:08:40.653 --> 00:08:41.654 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: That's right.

00:08:41.654 --> 00:08:42.588 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: --other than--

00:08:42.588 --> 00:08:46.826 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: It's getting
information from the future.

00:08:46.826 --> 00:08:49.396 align:middle line:84%
This is what we call a
premonition, essentially.

00:08:49.396 --> 00:08:53.366 align:middle line:84%
The body knows something
that hasn't happened yet.

00:08:53.366 --> 00:08:55.435 align:middle line:84%
These studies have been
replicated by researchers

00:08:55.435 --> 00:08:56.569 align:middle line:90%
all over the world.

00:08:56.569 --> 00:08:58.204 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I'm sure our
viewers can relate

00:08:58.204 --> 00:08:59.406 align:middle line:90%
with this as they're talking.

00:08:59.406 --> 00:09:01.875 align:middle line:84%
If you have had these
types of premonitions,

00:09:01.875 --> 00:09:03.076 align:middle line:90%
let us know via Facebook.

00:09:03.076 --> 00:09:05.478 align:middle line:84%
It'd be interesting to get
the feedback from the viewers.

00:09:05.478 --> 00:09:08.047 align:middle line:84%
This has apparently been spoken
about in ancient history.

00:09:08.047 --> 00:09:10.316 align:middle line:84%
There's been a lot of
prophecy about this.

00:09:10.316 --> 00:09:11.484 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Well, exactly.

00:09:11.484 --> 00:09:13.653 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people think
that premonitions are just

00:09:13.653 --> 00:09:16.289 align:middle line:84%
kind of a modern kind of a
deal, but in the Old Testament

00:09:16.289 --> 00:09:19.926 align:middle line:90%
they were called prophecy.

00:09:19.926 --> 00:09:22.495 align:middle line:84%
Shamanism goes back
for 50,000 years.

00:09:22.495 --> 00:09:28.368 align:middle line:84%
And any decent shaman had
powers of foreknowledge,

00:09:28.368 --> 00:09:31.638 align:middle line:84%
knowing where the enemy would
be, where game was located--

00:09:31.638 --> 00:09:32.539 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, of course.

00:09:32.539 --> 00:09:32.705 align:middle line:90%
That--

00:09:32.705 --> 00:09:34.974 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: --where shelter
was, and this sort of thing.

00:09:34.974 --> 00:09:38.111 align:middle line:84%
So this has been part
of the human legacy

00:09:38.111 --> 00:09:40.180 align:middle line:90%
for at least 50,000 years.

00:09:40.180 --> 00:09:42.449 align:middle line:84%
And it's only in the
past few hundred years

00:09:42.449 --> 00:09:45.118 align:middle line:84%
that we've disowned this
and said it's impossible,

00:09:45.118 --> 00:09:46.586 align:middle line:90%
can't happen.

00:09:46.586 --> 00:09:48.855 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: What do the scientists
say about the studies

00:09:48.855 --> 00:09:53.460 align:middle line:84%
by Dean Radin, the quantum
entanglement studies?

00:09:53.460 --> 00:09:57.564 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Actually, there's
a huge debate over them now.

00:09:57.564 --> 00:10:03.570 align:middle line:84%
And a doctor named Daryl
Bem at Cornell University

00:10:03.570 --> 00:10:05.171 align:middle line:90%
has done nine of these himself.

00:10:05.171 --> 00:10:07.407 align:middle line:90%
Eight of them came out positive.

00:10:07.407 --> 00:10:08.508 align:middle line:90%
And it's just thrown--

00:10:08.508 --> 00:10:09.342 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:10:09.342 --> 00:10:11.811 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: --it's just thrown
the skeptics for a loop.

00:10:11.811 --> 00:10:13.780 align:middle line:84%
There are all sorts of
arguments about this.

00:10:13.780 --> 00:10:14.714 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:10:14.714 --> 00:10:17.383 align:middle line:84%
Well, apparently
science has attempted

00:10:17.383 --> 00:10:19.085 align:middle line:84%
to prove it many,
many different ways.

00:10:19.085 --> 00:10:20.620 align:middle line:84%
We have a slide here
that shows that.

00:10:20.620 --> 00:10:21.888 align:middle line:90%
What's the story behind that?

00:10:21.888 --> 00:10:23.423 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, the
story behind that

00:10:23.423 --> 00:10:26.359 align:middle line:84%
is that that was
one of my patients

00:10:26.359 --> 00:10:31.064 align:middle line:84%
who was a well known
attorney in Dallas.

00:10:31.064 --> 00:10:34.000 align:middle line:84%
She came, knocked on my door
one morning, and she said,

00:10:34.000 --> 00:10:34.868 align:middle line:90%
I'm scared to death.

00:10:34.868 --> 00:10:37.670 align:middle line:90%
I need your help.

00:10:37.670 --> 00:10:39.672 align:middle line:84%
Her story was that she
had had a dream the night

00:10:39.672 --> 00:10:42.375 align:middle line:84%
before that she
had, as she said,

00:10:42.375 --> 00:10:46.446 align:middle line:84%
three little white
spots on her left ovary.

00:10:46.446 --> 00:10:49.582 align:middle line:84%
And she said, I know
I've got ovarian cancer.

00:10:49.582 --> 00:10:50.717 align:middle line:90%
And I'm just terrified.

00:10:50.717 --> 00:10:51.684 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Out of the blue?

00:10:51.684 --> 00:10:53.319 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Out of the blue.

00:10:53.319 --> 00:10:55.054 align:middle line:90%
So I did a pelvic examination.

00:10:55.054 --> 00:10:56.356 align:middle line:90%
It was completely normal.

00:10:56.356 --> 00:11:03.162 align:middle line:84%
We decided to do a sonogram to
resolve her fears and anxiety.

00:11:03.162 --> 00:11:07.200 align:middle line:84%
And sure enough,
the sonogram reports

00:11:07.200 --> 00:11:12.272 align:middle line:84%
showed that she had three little
white spots on her left ovary,

00:11:12.272 --> 00:11:13.473 align:middle line:90%
just as she had dreamt.

00:11:13.473 --> 00:11:16.142 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And this was a
picture of that sonogram?

00:11:16.142 --> 00:11:17.744 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: That's not
the specific one,

00:11:17.744 --> 00:11:21.214 align:middle line:84%
but this is one just for
illustrative purposes,

00:11:21.214 --> 00:11:22.115 align:middle line:90%
showing a sonogram.

00:11:22.115 --> 00:11:22.248 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:11:22.248 --> 00:11:23.249 align:middle line:90%
Interesting.

00:11:23.249 --> 00:11:26.185 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: But she had no
business knowing this.

00:11:26.185 --> 00:11:28.354 align:middle line:90%
She had no symptoms whatsoever.

00:11:28.354 --> 00:11:30.823 align:middle line:90%
And she wasn't the only one.

00:11:30.823 --> 00:11:35.995 align:middle line:84%
Other equally interesting
and unlikely reports

00:11:35.995 --> 00:11:40.967 align:middle line:84%
of premonitions begin to
filter in from other people.

00:11:40.967 --> 00:11:44.637 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you think that
the nurses and the doctors--

00:11:44.637 --> 00:11:48.641 align:middle line:84%
the nurses tend to have the
premonitions-- I wouldn't say

00:11:48.641 --> 00:11:53.212 align:middle line:84%
more than the doctors, but that
they tend to report them more?

00:11:53.212 --> 00:11:54.113 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Absolutely.

00:11:54.113 --> 00:11:54.747 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:11:54.747 --> 00:11:58.851 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: My wife Barbara is
a cardiovascular and holistic

00:11:58.851 --> 00:12:02.255 align:middle line:84%
nurse, and I've lived
with stories of nurses

00:12:02.255 --> 00:12:04.457 align:middle line:84%
and their premonitions
for 40 years.

00:12:04.457 --> 00:12:08.194 align:middle line:84%
And I must say, I don't
know of any profession that

00:12:08.194 --> 00:12:11.931 align:middle line:84%
is more premonition
prone than nurses.

00:12:11.931 --> 00:12:15.435 align:middle line:84%
They spend their professional
lives at the bedside,

00:12:15.435 --> 00:12:17.437 align:middle line:84%
developing some sort
of intuitive skill

00:12:17.437 --> 00:12:19.606 align:middle line:90%
that just eludes doctors.

00:12:19.606 --> 00:12:21.107 align:middle line:84%
And they're not as
reluctant to talk

00:12:21.107 --> 00:12:23.176 align:middle line:90%
about it as physicians are.

00:12:23.176 --> 00:12:26.512 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And so they do have
more of maybe a relationship

00:12:26.512 --> 00:12:30.783 align:middle line:84%
with these people in a--
maybe that's what creates it.

00:12:30.783 --> 00:12:32.518 align:middle line:84%
When you have a
relationship with someone,

00:12:32.518 --> 00:12:34.721 align:middle line:90%
is the premonition heightened?

00:12:34.721 --> 00:12:36.623 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I think that
that's exactly right.

00:12:36.623 --> 00:12:38.324 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Has that been proven?

00:12:38.324 --> 00:12:39.058 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Yes.

00:12:39.058 --> 00:12:41.961 align:middle line:84%
People who have intimate
relations with other people

00:12:41.961 --> 00:12:45.698 align:middle line:84%
tend to be on their wavelength
more and are able, I think,

00:12:45.698 --> 00:12:49.669 align:middle line:84%
to acquire premonition-type
experiences.

00:12:49.669 --> 00:12:51.404 align:middle line:90%
So, yes.

00:12:51.404 --> 00:12:57.176 align:middle line:84%
And we physicians are terribly
left brained, analytical,

00:12:57.176 --> 00:13:00.113 align:middle line:84%
and logical and all
this sort of thing.

00:13:00.113 --> 00:13:01.881 align:middle line:90%
And we take pride in that.

00:13:01.881 --> 00:13:04.884 align:middle line:84%
I think nurses have a more
general way of knowing.

00:13:04.884 --> 00:13:09.389 align:middle line:84%
They're not locked into their
intellectual ability, which

00:13:09.389 --> 00:13:12.425 align:middle line:84%
doesn't really help
you have premonition.

00:13:12.425 --> 00:13:15.228 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Maybe more
permission for having

00:13:15.228 --> 00:13:16.729 align:middle line:90%
that kind of a conversation.

00:13:16.729 --> 00:13:19.065 align:middle line:84%
So has the science
of premonitions

00:13:19.065 --> 00:13:23.136 align:middle line:84%
reached its way into
the medical community?

00:13:23.136 --> 00:13:24.837 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I think it's
always been there.

00:13:24.837 --> 00:13:26.973 align:middle line:84%
I just think that
doctors have been

00:13:26.973 --> 00:13:29.876 align:middle line:84%
really shy about
talking about it.

00:13:29.876 --> 00:13:32.211 align:middle line:84%
Just as an example, when
I was in medical school,

00:13:32.211 --> 00:13:35.081 align:middle line:84%
I had a couple of
professors who were

00:13:35.081 --> 00:13:39.419 align:middle line:84%
able to make these uncanny
diagnoses in ways I just simply

00:13:39.419 --> 00:13:40.253 align:middle line:90%
couldn't figure out.

00:13:40.253 --> 00:13:43.623 align:middle line:84%
And when I would ask them
how they made the diagnosis

00:13:43.623 --> 00:13:45.758 align:middle line:84%
in a particular
case, one of them

00:13:45.758 --> 00:13:47.193 align:middle line:90%
was simply unable to explain.

00:13:47.193 --> 00:13:50.463 align:middle line:84%
He just sort of laughed it
off and he said, oh, it's

00:13:50.463 --> 00:13:51.631 align:middle line:90%
just a matter of experience.

00:13:54.901 --> 00:13:58.004 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Right, the really good
doctors or practitioners I know

00:13:58.004 --> 00:14:00.073 align:middle line:90%
are amazing diagnosticians.

00:14:00.073 --> 00:14:01.174 align:middle line:90%
And that's probably why.

00:14:01.174 --> 00:14:03.176 align:middle line:84%
They're connected
to their intuition.

00:14:03.176 --> 00:14:06.746 align:middle line:84%
And it goes against the
conventional medical view,

00:14:06.746 --> 00:14:08.848 align:middle line:90%
that was what?

00:14:08.848 --> 00:14:10.583 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well it's
that you just have

00:14:10.583 --> 00:14:11.784 align:middle line:90%
to reason through the facts.

00:14:11.784 --> 00:14:15.521 align:middle line:84%
You have to do an examination,
take a history, do the test,

00:14:15.521 --> 00:14:18.758 align:middle line:84%
and put the pieces together
in a logical order.

00:14:18.758 --> 00:14:20.893 align:middle line:84%
Well, premonitions aren't
about going from point A

00:14:20.893 --> 00:14:23.529 align:middle line:84%
to point B to point C.
They're like jumping from A

00:14:23.529 --> 00:14:28.735 align:middle line:84%
to Z without any intervening
logical, analytical framework.

00:14:28.735 --> 00:14:31.704 align:middle line:84%
And I think that makes a lot
of intellectually-oriented

00:14:31.704 --> 00:14:34.140 align:middle line:90%
physicians really nervous.

00:14:34.140 --> 00:14:39.045 align:middle line:84%
Because we're trained that that
is not the right way to do it.

00:14:39.045 --> 00:14:40.480 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yeah, it
does take away all

00:14:40.480 --> 00:14:42.582 align:middle line:84%
of the training, the medical
school, and so forth.

00:14:42.582 --> 00:14:45.051 align:middle line:84%
But as we see here, that
the conventional view is

00:14:45.051 --> 00:14:47.553 align:middle line:84%
that the mind is
confined to the brain.

00:14:47.553 --> 00:14:50.123 align:middle line:84%
And there's nothing outside
of that mind, right?

00:14:50.123 --> 00:14:51.090 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Right.

00:14:51.090 --> 00:14:54.227 align:middle line:84%
And so premonitions suggest
that there is something outside.

00:14:54.227 --> 00:14:55.094 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:14:55.094 --> 00:14:57.296 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: You can know
something without putting

00:14:57.296 --> 00:14:59.932 align:middle line:84%
the pieces together
intellectually

00:14:59.932 --> 00:15:01.367 align:middle line:90%
and analytically.

00:15:01.367 --> 00:15:04.971 align:middle line:84%
And also, one reason that we
say you can't have a premonition

00:15:04.971 --> 00:15:07.573 align:middle line:84%
is because of the
way we view time.

00:15:07.573 --> 00:15:11.878 align:middle line:84%
We say time flows like a river
from the past into the present

00:15:11.878 --> 00:15:13.513 align:middle line:90%
and into the future.

00:15:13.513 --> 00:15:16.048 align:middle line:84%
And a premonition suggests
that well, maybe time

00:15:16.048 --> 00:15:18.985 align:middle line:84%
might come back
in this direction,

00:15:18.985 --> 00:15:21.354 align:middle line:84%
bringing information
from the future

00:15:21.354 --> 00:15:25.358 align:middle line:84%
into the present, which you
might sense as a premonition.

00:15:25.358 --> 00:15:26.893 align:middle line:90%
We know that can't happen.

00:15:26.893 --> 00:15:27.994 align:middle line:90%
Time can't flow backwards.

00:15:27.994 --> 00:15:29.562 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The river
can't flow back up.

00:15:29.562 --> 00:15:30.363 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Flow
backwards-- exactly.

00:15:30.363 --> 00:15:31.364 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah, exactly.

00:15:31.364 --> 00:15:33.266 align:middle line:84%
However, there has
been science then

00:15:33.266 --> 00:15:37.003 align:middle line:84%
that has proven that
premonitions are possible.

00:15:37.003 --> 00:15:38.037 align:middle line:90%
Explain that.

00:15:38.037 --> 00:15:41.073 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, there
are several efforts

00:15:41.073 --> 00:15:47.513 align:middle line:84%
in physics now to develop
models of time which

00:15:47.513 --> 00:15:49.182 align:middle line:90%
are premonition friendly.

00:15:49.182 --> 00:15:51.951 align:middle line:84%
In physics this is
called retrocausation.

00:15:51.951 --> 00:15:55.188 align:middle line:84%
And this is a hot
topic in physics.

00:15:55.188 --> 00:15:59.759 align:middle line:84%
And it presents a model that's
cordial to having premonitions.

00:15:59.759 --> 00:16:02.328 align:middle line:84%
There are several ways
that they talk about this.

00:16:02.328 --> 00:16:05.398 align:middle line:84%
One is that there may
be a block universe.

00:16:05.398 --> 00:16:06.699 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: What's a block universe?

00:16:06.699 --> 00:16:08.367 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: A block
universe is a universe

00:16:08.367 --> 00:16:11.571 align:middle line:84%
in which everything that
has happened or will happen

00:16:11.571 --> 00:16:15.041 align:middle line:90%
has already-- already exists.

00:16:15.041 --> 00:16:18.578 align:middle line:84%
And if this is so, if that
information of future events

00:16:18.578 --> 00:16:20.279 align:middle line:84%
has already happened,
then it might

00:16:20.279 --> 00:16:22.882 align:middle line:84%
be possible for consciousness
to acquire information

00:16:22.882 --> 00:16:26.319 align:middle line:84%
about that, which you would
experience as a premonition.

00:16:26.319 --> 00:16:28.187 align:middle line:90%
Another-- I know this is weird--

00:16:28.187 --> 00:16:30.056 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: No, no, no, no, no--
this is very interesting to me.

00:16:30.056 --> 00:16:31.324 align:middle line:90%
This is extremely interesting.

00:16:31.324 --> 00:16:33.392 align:middle line:84%
So, there's so much that
goes along with this.

00:16:33.392 --> 00:16:37.296 align:middle line:84%
So this essentially suggests, in
the theory of quantum physics,

00:16:37.296 --> 00:16:41.167 align:middle line:84%
that there can be parallel
universes, future universes--

00:16:41.167 --> 00:16:42.235 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Retrocausation.

00:16:42.235 --> 00:16:44.036 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Retrocausation.

00:16:44.036 --> 00:16:45.271 align:middle line:90%
And this has been proven?

00:16:45.271 --> 00:16:46.305 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Well, this is--

00:16:46.305 --> 00:16:47.540 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How you can
possibly prove that.

00:16:47.540 --> 00:16:48.241 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well,
these are hypotheses.

00:16:48.241 --> 00:16:49.342 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:16:49.342 --> 00:16:51.978 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: And Lord knows
which one will eventually

00:16:51.978 --> 00:16:53.746 align:middle line:90%
float to the top, if any.

00:16:53.746 --> 00:16:56.148 align:middle line:84%
But this is taken
very seriously.

00:16:56.148 --> 00:17:00.186 align:middle line:84%
Now is not just a philosophical
plaything for physicists.

00:17:00.186 --> 00:17:02.788 align:middle line:84%
They are dead serious
about these possibilities.

00:17:02.788 --> 00:17:07.425 align:middle line:84%
And another is what physicists
call closed timelike loops,

00:17:07.425 --> 00:17:10.061 align:middle line:84%
in which time might circle
back from the future

00:17:10.061 --> 00:17:12.698 align:middle line:84%
into the present, bringing
future information

00:17:12.698 --> 00:17:16.335 align:middle line:84%
into the present that you might
experience as a premonition.

00:17:16.335 --> 00:17:20.172 align:middle line:84%
This is taken dead
seriously by physicists.

00:17:20.172 --> 00:17:27.079 align:middle line:84%
So there are models that permit
premonitions on the horizon.

00:17:27.079 --> 00:17:27.914 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:17:27.914 --> 00:17:29.215 align:middle line:90%
I can't wait for that.

00:17:29.215 --> 00:17:31.450 align:middle line:84%
Does this explain
a deja vu, maybe?

00:17:31.450 --> 00:17:33.286 align:middle line:84%
Facebook listeners are
asking that question.

00:17:33.286 --> 00:17:34.720 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Well, sure.

00:17:34.720 --> 00:17:38.724 align:middle line:84%
Deja vu is a sense
that something

00:17:38.724 --> 00:17:40.860 align:middle line:84%
that-- you're
experiencing something

00:17:40.860 --> 00:17:42.161 align:middle line:90%
that has already happened.

00:17:42.161 --> 00:17:44.630 align:middle line:84%
And the model of
the block universe

00:17:44.630 --> 00:17:50.403 align:middle line:84%
is certainly one way to
accommodate that sort of thing.

00:17:50.403 --> 00:17:53.272 align:middle line:84%
Premonitions are a sense
of what will happen.

00:17:53.272 --> 00:17:56.108 align:middle line:84%
Deja vu is a sense that
what you're experiencing

00:17:56.108 --> 00:17:57.977 align:middle line:90%
has already happened.

00:17:57.977 --> 00:18:01.247 align:middle line:84%
But in a block
universe, the phenomena

00:18:01.247 --> 00:18:02.915 align:middle line:90%
seem to be very related.

00:18:02.915 --> 00:18:03.916 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:18:03.916 --> 00:18:05.351 align:middle line:84%
One of the other
Facebook listeners

00:18:05.351 --> 00:18:07.753 align:middle line:84%
was asking if that
could create healing,

00:18:07.753 --> 00:18:10.823 align:middle line:84%
if they could create
healing with premonitions.

00:18:10.823 --> 00:18:12.024 align:middle line:90%
Does that make sense?

00:18:12.024 --> 00:18:15.962 align:middle line:84%
Nicole says, how can the power
of thought affect your health?

00:18:15.962 --> 00:18:18.264 align:middle line:84%
For instance, I'm thinking,
I don't feel so well today.

00:18:18.264 --> 00:18:20.999 align:middle line:84%
So does that encourage low
energy and poor health?

00:18:20.999 --> 00:18:22.034 align:middle line:90%
Can it be used like that?

00:18:22.034 --> 00:18:24.971 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, here's
one way that premonitions

00:18:24.971 --> 00:18:27.506 align:middle line:84%
might be of value
in creating health.

00:18:27.506 --> 00:18:29.809 align:middle line:84%
And I think this gets
played out in real life.

00:18:29.809 --> 00:18:34.013 align:middle line:84%
Let's say you have a
premonition that you're

00:18:34.013 --> 00:18:36.782 align:middle line:84%
going to have an automobile
accident tomorrow-- not so good

00:18:36.782 --> 00:18:38.484 align:middle line:90%
for your health.

00:18:38.484 --> 00:18:41.120 align:middle line:84%
Well, what we believe
about premonitions

00:18:41.120 --> 00:18:44.690 align:middle line:84%
is that if you
have one like that,

00:18:44.690 --> 00:18:47.827 align:middle line:84%
that auto accident is
not written in stone.

00:18:47.827 --> 00:18:51.630 align:middle line:84%
It is not certain that
that has to happen.

00:18:51.630 --> 00:18:54.867 align:middle line:84%
We talk about a
probabilistic future.

00:18:54.867 --> 00:18:59.638 align:middle line:84%
That auto accident may indeed
be probable, and statistically

00:18:59.638 --> 00:19:02.174 align:middle line:84%
likely, but you can
shift statistics.

00:19:02.174 --> 00:19:05.644 align:middle line:84%
You can shift probabilities by
taking action in the present.

00:19:05.644 --> 00:19:08.347 align:middle line:84%
So you might be doubly careful
tomorrow when you go out

00:19:08.347 --> 00:19:12.084 align:middle line:84%
and drive and
eliminate that event

00:19:12.084 --> 00:19:14.153 align:middle line:90%
from happening in your life.

00:19:14.153 --> 00:19:18.758 align:middle line:84%
I think that gets played out
all the time in people's lives.

00:19:18.758 --> 00:19:19.925 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's so interesting.

00:19:19.925 --> 00:19:21.961 align:middle line:84%
So if there is this
block universe,

00:19:21.961 --> 00:19:24.497 align:middle line:84%
and if you can
essentially connect

00:19:24.497 --> 00:19:26.632 align:middle line:84%
through a premonition to
something that has already

00:19:26.632 --> 00:19:30.703 align:middle line:84%
happened, and possibly
connect to the back-- what

00:19:30.703 --> 00:19:35.708 align:middle line:84%
has happened in the past, then
can you not create the future?

00:19:35.708 --> 00:19:37.877 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I think
that's exactly right.

00:19:37.877 --> 00:19:40.446 align:middle line:84%
And I think this
is one reason why

00:19:40.446 --> 00:19:42.782 align:middle line:84%
we should be talking
about premonitions.

00:19:42.782 --> 00:19:44.150 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people
think that if you

00:19:44.150 --> 00:19:46.152 align:middle line:84%
have a premonition that
something horrible is

00:19:46.152 --> 00:19:48.254 align:middle line:90%
going to happen.

00:19:48.254 --> 00:19:50.222 align:middle line:84%
It's going to happen,
and you're just

00:19:50.222 --> 00:19:53.459 align:middle line:84%
getting a preview of
something terrible.

00:19:53.459 --> 00:19:55.594 align:middle line:84%
Well, that's only
one part of it.

00:19:55.594 --> 00:19:57.897 align:middle line:84%
The good part of it
is that this idea

00:19:57.897 --> 00:20:01.700 align:middle line:84%
of the probabilistic
future that can be changed.

00:20:01.700 --> 00:20:04.270 align:middle line:84%
It's trivial to say, I think
these days, as many people do,

00:20:04.270 --> 00:20:06.305 align:middle line:84%
that you create
your own reality.

00:20:06.305 --> 00:20:08.274 align:middle line:84%
I'm not sure you
create all of it.

00:20:08.274 --> 00:20:12.278 align:middle line:84%
But I know this-- the data
suggests very strongly that you

00:20:12.278 --> 00:20:15.014 align:middle line:84%
can influence it and
shift the probability

00:20:15.014 --> 00:20:18.150 align:middle line:84%
from a horrible future
into one that's benign.

00:20:18.150 --> 00:20:20.586 align:middle line:84%
And in that way, we can
talk about preventing

00:20:20.586 --> 00:20:22.021 align:middle line:90%
horrible things happening to us.

00:20:22.021 --> 00:20:22.855 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Fascinating.

00:20:22.855 --> 00:20:24.557 align:middle line:84%
So there's an
interesting statistic

00:20:24.557 --> 00:20:27.726 align:middle line:84%
I didn't know about
the airplanes that

00:20:27.726 --> 00:20:30.362 align:middle line:84%
went into the World
Trade Center on 9/11.

00:20:30.362 --> 00:20:32.164 align:middle line:90%
Can you share that with us?

00:20:32.164 --> 00:20:33.532 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well,
I think Americans

00:20:33.532 --> 00:20:39.205 align:middle line:84%
have some very erroneous ideas
about what happened on 9/11.

00:20:39.205 --> 00:20:40.372 align:middle line:90%
Actually, I was one of them.

00:20:40.372 --> 00:20:45.744 align:middle line:84%
I think many of us think that
four jam-packed commercial jets

00:20:45.744 --> 00:20:50.783 align:middle line:90%
flew into the towers or crashed.

00:20:50.783 --> 00:20:53.552 align:middle line:90%
And that simply wasn't the case.

00:20:53.552 --> 00:20:58.224 align:middle line:90%
Those planes were 79% empty.

00:20:58.224 --> 00:20:59.492 align:middle line:90%
This is public knowledge, this.

00:20:59.492 --> 00:21:00.426 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Who knew that?

00:21:00.426 --> 00:21:02.528 align:middle line:90%
They were 79% empty?

00:21:02.528 --> 00:21:03.929 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: That's exactly right.

00:21:03.929 --> 00:21:07.433 align:middle line:84%
One of the plains
was only 16% full.

00:21:07.433 --> 00:21:10.836 align:middle line:84%
None of them were
more than half full.

00:21:10.836 --> 00:21:13.806 align:middle line:84%
And so this is a
fascinating statistic

00:21:13.806 --> 00:21:17.710 align:middle line:84%
that takes most people by
surprise, as it did me.

00:21:17.710 --> 00:21:20.779 align:middle line:84%
Actually, I didn't believe this
when I found the statistics.

00:21:20.779 --> 00:21:23.916 align:middle line:84%
But it's in the
congressional 9/11 report.

00:21:23.916 --> 00:21:26.418 align:middle line:84%
Anyone can look up these
statistics for themselves.

00:21:26.418 --> 00:21:30.489 align:middle line:84%
And so it leads you to ask,
why were those planes so empty?

00:21:30.489 --> 00:21:32.024 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yeah.

00:21:32.024 --> 00:21:35.027 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: It would appear on
the surface that a lot of people

00:21:35.027 --> 00:21:38.597 align:middle line:84%
found some reason not
to travel that day.

00:21:38.597 --> 00:21:40.099 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Actually,
Gina, the producer

00:21:40.099 --> 00:21:42.301 align:middle line:84%
of the show, shared with
me three stories of three

00:21:42.301 --> 00:21:43.736 align:middle line:84%
friends of hers
that were supposed

00:21:43.736 --> 00:21:47.239 align:middle line:84%
to have been in that building
that day, that kids sick,

00:21:47.239 --> 00:21:50.376 align:middle line:84%
or something else
happened, or different part

00:21:50.376 --> 00:21:51.277 align:middle line:90%
of town, randomly.

00:21:51.277 --> 00:21:52.945 align:middle line:84%
They were all
supposed to be there.

00:21:52.945 --> 00:21:54.380 align:middle line:90%
She knows three of them.

00:21:54.380 --> 00:21:55.080 align:middle line:90%
Yeah.

00:21:55.080 --> 00:21:58.517 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, here's something
else that I'm fascinated by.

00:21:58.517 --> 00:22:04.623 align:middle line:84%
If you talk to people who
have cancelled their flights,

00:22:04.623 --> 00:22:07.459 align:middle line:84%
or rearranged their schedules,
and then the plane went

00:22:07.459 --> 00:22:11.664 align:middle line:84%
on to crash, almost never
will those people say,

00:22:11.664 --> 00:22:14.466 align:middle line:84%
I had a premonition
of a plane crash.

00:22:14.466 --> 00:22:17.603 align:middle line:84%
And this is where the
unconscious comes in, I think.

00:22:17.603 --> 00:22:22.775 align:middle line:84%
What people will say is, I
don't know why I cancelled it.

00:22:22.775 --> 00:22:27.346 align:middle line:84%
I just had a feeling that I
just should not fly that day.

00:22:27.346 --> 00:22:29.248 align:middle line:84%
I just didn't feel
right about it.

00:22:29.248 --> 00:22:30.950 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Or events like
a child gets sick,

00:22:30.950 --> 00:22:32.384 align:middle line:90%
or something like that.

00:22:32.384 --> 00:22:35.054 align:middle line:84%
Do you think that all plays into
the whole idea of premonitions?

00:22:35.054 --> 00:22:36.522 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Absolutely.

00:22:36.522 --> 00:22:38.190 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: How could you--

00:22:38.190 --> 00:22:42.061 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I think that this is
largely an unconscious process.

00:22:42.061 --> 00:22:44.563 align:middle line:84%
What I think is going
on-- this is an idea

00:22:44.563 --> 00:22:47.466 align:middle line:84%
that's been put forward by a
cognitive psychologist, Dr.

00:22:47.466 --> 00:22:53.606 align:middle line:84%
James Carpenter-- he says that
these premonitions work very

00:22:53.606 --> 00:22:57.543 align:middle line:84%
subtly in our lives, usually at
the subconscious or unconscious

00:22:57.543 --> 00:23:00.212 align:middle line:84%
level, as there's a
lot of evidence for.

00:23:00.212 --> 00:23:04.316 align:middle line:84%
And he says, we ought to stop
calling this second sight.

00:23:04.316 --> 00:23:08.053 align:middle line:84%
Generations ago, this was called
second sight, in medieval times

00:23:08.053 --> 00:23:09.154 align:middle line:90%
especially.

00:23:09.154 --> 00:23:11.890 align:middle line:84%
And he says we need to start
calling it first sight.

00:23:11.890 --> 00:23:12.725 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:23:12.725 --> 00:23:14.793 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: He said because
this is so fundamental;

00:23:14.793 --> 00:23:17.096 align:middle line:84%
it's even more
fundamental than vision.

00:23:17.096 --> 00:23:20.466 align:middle line:84%
And it operates off
the scene of awareness,

00:23:20.466 --> 00:23:22.034 align:middle line:90%
in the unconscious level.

00:23:22.034 --> 00:23:25.204 align:middle line:84%
And therefore, we see people
canceling and rearranging

00:23:25.204 --> 00:23:29.508 align:middle line:84%
flights for reasons that
they're not totally sure about.

00:23:29.508 --> 00:23:30.643 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It's interesting.

00:23:30.643 --> 00:23:31.844 align:middle line:90%
Right, it's very interesting.

00:23:31.844 --> 00:23:35.414 align:middle line:84%
We have some examples of how
some of these premonitions

00:23:35.414 --> 00:23:37.082 align:middle line:90%
come true.

00:23:37.082 --> 00:23:41.086 align:middle line:84%
There's agencies and there's
bureaus of premonitions.

00:23:41.086 --> 00:23:42.187 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: That's right.

00:23:42.187 --> 00:23:43.255 align:middle line:90%
And I think--

00:23:43.255 --> 00:23:44.957 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I never knew that.

00:23:44.957 --> 00:23:46.525 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Few people do.

00:23:46.525 --> 00:23:48.761 align:middle line:90%
But we can change that.

00:23:48.761 --> 00:23:49.395 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: We are.

00:23:49.395 --> 00:23:50.696 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: We are changing that.

00:23:50.696 --> 00:23:52.564 align:middle line:84%
I would like for
people to be aware

00:23:52.564 --> 00:23:56.035 align:middle line:84%
that they could contribute
to the research in this field

00:23:56.035 --> 00:23:59.905 align:middle line:84%
by reporting premonitions
of things that

00:23:59.905 --> 00:24:02.608 align:middle line:84%
would be in the interest of
the nation to know about,

00:24:02.608 --> 00:24:07.913 align:middle line:84%
such as terrorist attacks,
airline crashes, tsunamis,

00:24:07.913 --> 00:24:09.248 align:middle line:90%
earthquakes, and so on.

00:24:09.248 --> 00:24:10.749 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Is that why
the bureaus were

00:24:10.749 --> 00:24:11.583 align:middle line:90%
created in the first place?

00:24:11.583 --> 00:24:12.751 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Yes, that's right.

00:24:12.751 --> 00:24:17.289 align:middle line:84%
The question is, if we were
to collect these premonitions

00:24:17.289 --> 00:24:22.961 align:middle line:84%
and analyze it, could we predict
events which we would want

00:24:22.961 --> 00:24:26.298 align:middle line:84%
to predict, that we
would want to prevent,

00:24:26.298 --> 00:24:27.666 align:middle line:90%
such as a terrorist attack.

00:24:27.666 --> 00:24:31.804 align:middle line:84%
So there's an organization
called the Arlington Institute.

00:24:31.804 --> 00:24:34.273 align:middle line:84%
It's a think tank that's
run by John Petersen, who

00:24:34.273 --> 00:24:37.443 align:middle line:84%
is one of the most gifted
futurist predictors

00:24:37.443 --> 00:24:38.210 align:middle line:90%
in the country.

00:24:38.210 --> 00:24:38.911 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, yes.

00:24:38.911 --> 00:24:43.148 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: And so the website
is arlingtoninstitute.org.

00:24:43.148 --> 00:24:46.618 align:middle line:84%
So viewers, if you
have a premonition

00:24:46.618 --> 00:24:50.489 align:middle line:84%
you think needs to be
reported, log onto the website

00:24:50.489 --> 00:24:52.624 align:middle line:90%
and enter your premonition.

00:24:52.624 --> 00:24:54.193 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Global
types of situations?

00:24:54.193 --> 00:24:55.994 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Global or local
events-- either one.

00:24:55.994 --> 00:24:56.662 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:24:56.662 --> 00:24:58.030 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: And so
they have a team

00:24:58.030 --> 00:25:00.666 align:middle line:84%
of analysts and statisticians
who analyze these things.

00:25:00.666 --> 00:25:03.469 align:middle line:84%
And they call this
the whether map.

00:25:03.469 --> 00:25:07.206 align:middle line:84%
Now, this is not a
weather map, like climate.

00:25:07.206 --> 00:25:08.874 align:middle line:90%
They want to know whether--

00:25:08.874 --> 00:25:10.008 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Or not this could--

00:25:10.008 --> 00:25:14.680 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: --whether or not these
things can be put to good use.

00:25:14.680 --> 00:25:17.583 align:middle line:84%
So people can make a nice
contribution to this research

00:25:17.583 --> 00:25:18.317 align:middle line:90%
by doing this.

00:25:18.317 --> 00:25:19.718 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Interesting,
interesting.

00:25:19.718 --> 00:25:23.255 align:middle line:84%
Mark from Facebook is saying,
do premonitions most often

00:25:23.255 --> 00:25:23.956 align:middle line:90%
come in dreams?

00:25:23.956 --> 00:25:25.424 align:middle line:84%
And how can you
tell the difference

00:25:25.424 --> 00:25:29.194 align:middle line:84%
between a premonition
and a regular dream?

00:25:29.194 --> 00:25:32.664 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, premonitions
often come in dreams.

00:25:32.664 --> 00:25:35.401 align:middle line:84%
It depends on how you want
to define a premonition.

00:25:35.401 --> 00:25:38.504 align:middle line:84%
If you want to call it
intuition, or gut feelings,

00:25:38.504 --> 00:25:40.739 align:middle line:84%
or a hunch, a lot
of that takes place

00:25:40.739 --> 00:25:43.308 align:middle line:90%
in ordinary waking awareness.

00:25:43.308 --> 00:25:45.811 align:middle line:84%
But I must say that
those premonitions

00:25:45.811 --> 00:25:47.413 align:middle line:84%
sort of knock your
socks off, that

00:25:47.413 --> 00:25:53.819 align:middle line:84%
are really humdingers, complex--
about airlines crashing,

00:25:53.819 --> 00:25:56.054 align:middle line:84%
terrorist attacks, this sort
of thing-- those usually

00:25:56.054 --> 00:25:57.489 align:middle line:90%
crop up in dreams.

00:25:57.489 --> 00:25:59.324 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:25:59.324 --> 00:26:01.059 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: And so what
was Mark's next--

00:26:01.059 --> 00:26:03.629 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So, how do you tell
the difference between--

00:26:03.629 --> 00:26:04.797 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: A regular dream?

00:26:04.797 --> 00:26:06.064 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: A regular dream.

00:26:06.064 --> 00:26:07.999 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, there's
no 100% way to do this,

00:26:07.999 --> 00:26:11.403 align:middle line:84%
but there are
criteria that we can

00:26:11.403 --> 00:26:14.807 align:middle line:84%
use to separate
ordinary scary dreams--

00:26:14.807 --> 00:26:17.943 align:middle line:84%
this sort of thing-- or
nightmares, from the real deal.

00:26:17.943 --> 00:26:19.611 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: From what a
real premonition is.

00:26:19.611 --> 00:26:20.512 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Shall
we go into those.

00:26:20.512 --> 00:26:22.014 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yes, well actually we're
going to take a quick break.

00:26:22.014 --> 00:26:23.015 align:middle line:84%
And when we come
