And this is one of the
most interesting stories

00:26:59.585 --> 00:27:00.953 align:middle line:90%
that I've heard.

00:27:00.953 --> 00:27:03.388 align:middle line:84%
I had not heard this before,
about the Westside Baptist

00:27:03.388 --> 00:27:04.556 align:middle line:90%
Church.

00:27:04.556 --> 00:27:05.257 align:middle line:90%
Fascinating.

00:27:05.257 --> 00:27:06.191 align:middle line:90%
What happened?

00:27:06.191 --> 00:27:11.864 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, on March 1,
1950, an event happened which

00:27:11.864 --> 00:27:14.366 align:middle line:84%
for a few days
electrified the country.

00:27:14.366 --> 00:27:17.369 align:middle line:84%
This was written up
in Life Magazine.

00:27:17.369 --> 00:27:19.705 align:middle line:84%
It captivated
people's attention.

00:27:19.705 --> 00:27:24.409 align:middle line:84%
What happened is that in this
little church in Southeastern

00:27:24.409 --> 00:27:27.980 align:middle line:84%
Nebraska, little
town called Beatrice,

00:27:27.980 --> 00:27:31.216 align:middle line:84%
there was a church, the
Westside Baptist Church.

00:27:31.216 --> 00:27:33.685 align:middle line:84%
And the Westside Baptist
Church had a little choir.

00:27:33.685 --> 00:27:35.287 align:middle line:90%
It had 15 members.

00:27:35.287 --> 00:27:40.526 align:middle line:84%
And they met every
Wednesday night at 7:20

00:27:40.526 --> 00:27:42.794 align:middle line:90%
for choir practice.

00:27:42.794 --> 00:27:46.431 align:middle line:84%
Something really unusual
happened on that night.

00:27:46.431 --> 00:27:50.035 align:middle line:90%
At 7:25 the church exploded.

00:27:50.035 --> 00:27:52.571 align:middle line:84%
They determined later that
it was a natural gas leak.

00:27:52.571 --> 00:27:54.873 align:middle line:90%
But this demolished the church.

00:27:54.873 --> 00:27:57.442 align:middle line:84%
It actually broke windows
all throughout town.

00:27:57.442 --> 00:27:59.077 align:middle line:84%
It knocked a little
radio station off.

00:27:59.077 --> 00:28:01.313 align:middle line:90%
This was a big time explosion.

00:28:01.313 --> 00:28:03.415 align:middle line:84%
But the thing is that
no one was injured,

00:28:03.415 --> 00:28:06.618 align:middle line:90%
because no one was there.

00:28:06.618 --> 00:28:09.354 align:middle line:84%
For the first time in the
history of that church,

00:28:09.354 --> 00:28:11.290 align:middle line:90%
there was a complete no show.

00:28:11.290 --> 00:28:13.125 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Nobody showed
up for choir practice?

00:28:13.125 --> 00:28:14.259 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Nobody showed up.

00:28:14.259 --> 00:28:15.694 align:middle line:90%
Nobody was hurt.

00:28:15.694 --> 00:28:18.764 align:middle line:84%
And so word got out
around the country.

00:28:18.764 --> 00:28:24.236 align:middle line:84%
And Beatrice was invaded by
investigators and statisticians

00:28:24.236 --> 00:28:29.074 align:middle line:84%
and people who recognized this
as just an extraordinary event.

00:28:33.278 --> 00:28:36.148 align:middle line:84%
And so, if you ask these
people, as actually happened

00:28:36.148 --> 00:28:38.450 align:middle line:84%
by enterprising
reporters, why they

00:28:38.450 --> 00:28:41.386 align:middle line:84%
didn't go to church
that night, nobody

00:28:41.386 --> 00:28:43.388 align:middle line:84%
had a clue that the Church
was going to blow up.

00:28:43.388 --> 00:28:47.192 align:middle line:84%
This did not show up in the
form of premonitions or warnings

00:28:47.192 --> 00:28:50.162 align:middle line:84%
or foreknowledge
at all in anybody.

00:28:50.162 --> 00:28:53.432 align:middle line:84%
And they all attributed
their absence

00:28:53.432 --> 00:28:55.767 align:middle line:90%
to ordinary, mundane happenings.

00:28:55.767 --> 00:28:57.102 align:middle line:90%
Some of them were kind of funny.

00:28:57.102 --> 00:29:00.806 align:middle line:84%
One woman said she just fell
in love with her ironing

00:29:00.806 --> 00:29:03.609 align:middle line:84%
and she just got carried
away with her ironing.

00:29:03.609 --> 00:29:04.443 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:29:04.443 --> 00:29:07.412 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Two high school girls,
who were members of the choir,

00:29:07.412 --> 00:29:09.915 align:middle line:84%
said they just fell in love
with doing their homework.

00:29:09.915 --> 00:29:11.583 align:middle line:90%
I think that's kind of unusual.

00:29:11.583 --> 00:29:13.585 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's not something
you hear every day.

00:29:13.585 --> 00:29:14.252 align:middle line:90%
Yes, exactly.

00:29:14.252 --> 00:29:14.720 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: That's right.

00:29:14.720 --> 00:29:16.388 align:middle line:84%
And so everybody had
a mundane reason,

00:29:16.388 --> 00:29:19.358 align:middle line:84%
but nobody had any
clue that a disaster

00:29:19.358 --> 00:29:21.226 align:middle line:90%
was in store for the church.

00:29:21.226 --> 00:29:23.028 align:middle line:84%
And I think this is
absolutely fascinating

00:29:23.028 --> 00:29:26.632 align:middle line:84%
because this shows
how these things work

00:29:26.632 --> 00:29:29.034 align:middle line:90%
at an unconscious level, often.

00:29:29.034 --> 00:29:32.137 align:middle line:84%
Even when big time disasters
are in your future,

00:29:32.137 --> 00:29:34.139 align:middle line:84%
you don't always get a
clear picture of that.

00:29:34.139 --> 00:29:36.008 align:middle line:84%
It's just a kind of a
little nudge, you know,

00:29:36.008 --> 00:29:39.778 align:middle line:84%
and you'll find other
excuses not to be there.

00:29:39.778 --> 00:29:41.179 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And you
think this all has

00:29:41.179 --> 00:29:44.950 align:middle line:84%
to do with this quantum
field of entanglement?

00:29:44.950 --> 00:29:46.318 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I think
entanglement is

00:29:46.318 --> 00:29:51.390 align:middle line:84%
one of the best theories we
have going to explain this.

00:29:51.390 --> 00:29:54.993 align:middle line:84%
But I would be the first
to say that it's only

00:29:54.993 --> 00:29:57.195 align:middle line:84%
honest to say we don't know
how this works right now.

00:29:57.195 --> 00:29:59.464 align:middle line:84%
I love the idea of
closed time-like loops

00:29:59.464 --> 00:30:02.668 align:middle line:84%
also, bringing information
from the future to the present

00:30:02.668 --> 00:30:04.870 align:middle line:84%
that we would experience
as a premonition.

00:30:04.870 --> 00:30:06.471 align:middle line:84%
I don't know which
one of these things

00:30:06.471 --> 00:30:09.574 align:middle line:84%
is going to be the going
hypothesis, eventually.

00:30:09.574 --> 00:30:13.745 align:middle line:84%
I don't know that we really
need to struggle with that, so

00:30:13.745 --> 00:30:16.381 align:middle line:84%
much as we need to
simply recognize-- look,

00:30:16.381 --> 00:30:18.183 align:middle line:90%
this is a fact of our lives.

00:30:18.183 --> 00:30:21.053 align:middle line:84%
These things are
an absolute gift

00:30:21.053 --> 00:30:23.622 align:middle line:84%
that nature has
presented us with.

00:30:23.622 --> 00:30:28.527 align:middle line:84%
This ability to sense danger,
to avoid destruction and threats

00:30:28.527 --> 00:30:29.194 align:middle line:90%
to our health.

00:30:29.194 --> 00:30:33.031 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Is there a place for
God in this conversation?

00:30:33.031 --> 00:30:36.234 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well it's interesting
that if you asked the members

00:30:36.234 --> 00:30:38.336 align:middle line:90%
of the Westside Baptist Church--

00:30:38.336 --> 00:30:39.538 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: I'm sure.

00:30:39.538 --> 00:30:43.175 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: --how this happened,
all of them said, God did it.

00:30:43.175 --> 00:30:44.042 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Yes.

00:30:44.042 --> 00:30:45.644 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: I'm open to that.

00:30:45.644 --> 00:30:47.646 align:middle line:84%
The reason I don't
introduce God is

00:30:47.646 --> 00:30:50.849 align:middle line:84%
because science has no business
talking about the presence

00:30:50.849 --> 00:30:54.519 align:middle line:84%
or absence of God,
in my opinion.

00:30:54.519 --> 00:30:57.322 align:middle line:84%
I think there's some places
science has real trouble going.

00:30:57.322 --> 00:30:59.124 align:middle line:90%
And this is one them.

00:30:59.124 --> 00:31:01.693 align:middle line:90%
We don't have any God meters.

00:31:01.693 --> 00:31:03.595 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Right, there's
no way to quantify God.

00:31:03.595 --> 00:31:04.362 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Exactly.

00:31:04.362 --> 00:31:06.631 align:middle line:84%
We don't have a really
good God detector.

00:31:06.631 --> 00:31:08.200 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Except for
what you're talking

00:31:08.200 --> 00:31:10.235 align:middle line:84%
about-- the evidence
of premonitions.

00:31:10.235 --> 00:31:14.005 align:middle line:84%
It's one of the closest
ways I've seen it described.

00:31:14.005 --> 00:31:16.308 align:middle line:84%
Roberta from Facebook says
that she had a premonition

00:31:16.308 --> 00:31:18.877 align:middle line:84%
to go to a certain coffee shop,
where she would normally never

00:31:18.877 --> 00:31:19.377 align:middle line:90%
go.

00:31:19.377 --> 00:31:22.447 align:middle line:84%
She met a man there, gave him a
lead to the best work contract

00:31:22.447 --> 00:31:22.948 align:middle line:90%
ever.

00:31:22.948 --> 00:31:24.683 align:middle line:84%
Is that considered
a premonition?

00:31:24.683 --> 00:31:26.084 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well,
I think that this

00:31:26.084 --> 00:31:29.287 align:middle line:84%
is a possible example of what
we've just been talking about,

00:31:29.287 --> 00:31:32.491 align:middle line:84%
how these things can operate
at an unconscious level.

00:31:32.491 --> 00:31:33.658 align:middle line:90%
She didn't have to go there.

00:31:33.658 --> 00:31:34.226 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right.

00:31:34.226 --> 00:31:36.528 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: She probably had
some good, solid reasons

00:31:36.528 --> 00:31:40.966 align:middle line:84%
not to go there, to
meet a stranger that

00:31:40.966 --> 00:31:44.302 align:middle line:90%
was completely unknown to her.

00:31:44.302 --> 00:31:45.403 align:middle line:90%
But she did anyway.

00:31:45.403 --> 00:31:47.405 align:middle line:84%
And I think that this
is one of the ways

00:31:47.405 --> 00:31:51.276 align:middle line:84%
that premonitions occur
in a lot of people's lives

00:31:51.276 --> 00:31:52.878 align:middle line:84%
at an unconscious,
subconscious level.

00:31:52.878 --> 00:31:54.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So you can
actually help other people

00:31:54.880 --> 00:31:57.149 align:middle line:90%
if you follow the premonitions.

00:31:57.149 --> 00:31:59.751 align:middle line:84%
Let's find out how
do you recognize

00:31:59.751 --> 00:32:02.854 align:middle line:84%
if it's an actual premonition--
and you say premonition.

00:32:02.854 --> 00:32:04.456 align:middle line:90%
Explain why.

00:32:04.456 --> 00:32:07.159 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: It probably has
to do with my southern way

00:32:07.159 --> 00:32:09.261 align:middle line:84%
of speaking that I've never
been able to eliminate.

00:32:09.261 --> 00:32:10.862 align:middle line:90%
I don't know.

00:32:10.862 --> 00:32:13.765 align:middle line:84%
If you look at the
etymology, the origin,

00:32:13.765 --> 00:32:16.535 align:middle line:84%
of the word premonition,
it comes from Greek words,

00:32:16.535 --> 00:32:21.206 align:middle line:84%
meaning a warning
that comes before.

00:32:21.206 --> 00:32:25.076 align:middle line:84%
And the before we
usually call a pre,

00:32:25.076 --> 00:32:28.046 align:middle line:84%
like a preamble
or a pre anything.

00:32:28.046 --> 00:32:32.450 align:middle line:84%
So I just hang onto that long
E and call it a premonition.

00:32:32.450 --> 00:32:34.085 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: I thought
that was intentional.

00:32:34.085 --> 00:32:36.555 align:middle line:84%
Yeah, because I've commonly
heard it premonition.

00:32:36.555 --> 00:32:39.858 align:middle line:84%
OK, so what are some of the
ways to determine what--

00:32:39.858 --> 00:32:42.661 align:middle line:90%
if it is actually a premonition?

00:32:42.661 --> 00:32:45.597 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, there
are at least four clues,

00:32:45.597 --> 00:32:49.334 align:middle line:84%
I think, which can really help
us sort out the crazy nightmare

00:32:49.334 --> 00:32:53.738 align:middle line:84%
foolish stuff from something we
really should pay attention to.

00:32:53.738 --> 00:32:55.674 align:middle line:84%
And I think the
biggest clue of all

00:32:55.674 --> 00:32:57.676 align:middle line:90%
is the vividness of the dream.

00:32:57.676 --> 00:32:59.744 align:middle line:84%
If you talk to people
who have these knock

00:32:59.744 --> 00:33:03.381 align:middle line:84%
your socks off premonitions,
they will almost always

00:33:03.381 --> 00:33:07.252 align:middle line:84%
describe these as having
some special quality.

00:33:07.252 --> 00:33:10.255 align:middle line:84%
One woman told me
that they just seemed

00:33:10.255 --> 00:33:13.024 align:middle line:90%
to be lit up from the inside.

00:33:13.024 --> 00:33:16.962 align:middle line:84%
They just have a special
feel or glow to them.

00:33:16.962 --> 00:33:18.630 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And they're
really vivid, right?

00:33:18.630 --> 00:33:19.965 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Extremely vivid.

00:33:19.965 --> 00:33:23.702 align:middle line:84%
That was my experience with
the dream I mentioned earlier.

00:33:23.702 --> 00:33:26.471 align:middle line:84%
At the time, I thought this
was the most vivid dream

00:33:26.471 --> 00:33:29.875 align:middle line:84%
in my life, which made no
sense in terms of the content.

00:33:29.875 --> 00:33:32.210 align:middle line:90%
But it was special.

00:33:32.210 --> 00:33:35.213 align:middle line:84%
Another woman told me
these things that turn out

00:33:35.213 --> 00:33:38.683 align:middle line:84%
to be true, they come to her
in her dreams in italics.

00:33:38.683 --> 00:33:39.885 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh, really?

00:33:39.885 --> 00:33:41.486 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: As if there's some
special quality to them.

00:33:41.486 --> 00:33:42.087 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Words?

00:33:42.087 --> 00:33:43.355 align:middle line:90%
Interesting.

00:33:43.355 --> 00:33:45.991 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: So people
struggle to find

00:33:45.991 --> 00:33:48.193 align:middle line:84%
ways to describe this
sense of specialness.

00:33:48.193 --> 00:33:52.163 align:middle line:84%
But the vividness is, I
think, the best clue of all.

00:33:52.163 --> 00:33:53.198 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK and then the--

00:33:53.198 --> 00:33:54.399 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: There are others, too.

00:33:54.399 --> 00:33:56.034 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: The other
one is that they're--

00:33:56.034 --> 00:33:57.469 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: They're recurrent.

00:33:57.469 --> 00:34:00.305 align:middle line:84%
These things can come and
keep hammering at you, night

00:34:00.305 --> 00:34:01.640 align:middle line:90%
after night after night.

00:34:01.640 --> 00:34:04.276 align:middle line:84%
And if that happens,
that is a huge clue

00:34:04.276 --> 00:34:06.077 align:middle line:90%
that you better listen up.

00:34:06.077 --> 00:34:07.579 align:middle line:90%
Another clue is that if they--

00:34:07.579 --> 00:34:09.347 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That's how I
created my radio show,

00:34:09.347 --> 00:34:12.250 align:middle line:84%
was the recurrent dream
of the Aware Show.

00:34:12.250 --> 00:34:14.452 align:middle line:84%
It was a title that
just kept coming

00:34:14.452 --> 00:34:15.786 align:middle line:90%
in and coming in and coming in.

00:34:15.786 --> 00:34:17.188 align:middle line:84%
And I've done it
for 12 years now.

00:34:17.188 --> 00:34:17.455 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Wow.

00:34:17.455 --> 00:34:18.322 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: So that's interesting.

00:34:18.322 --> 00:34:19.024 align:middle line:90%
So that was a--

00:34:19.024 --> 00:34:19.824 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well your
viewers should be happy

00:34:19.824 --> 00:34:21.626 align:middle line:84%
that you paid attention
to that premonitory dream.

00:34:21.626 --> 00:34:23.495 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Very interesting,
very interesting.

00:34:23.495 --> 00:34:25.196 align:middle line:84%
I never really thought
about it that way.

00:34:25.196 --> 00:34:26.231 align:middle line:90%
OK, another quality?

00:34:26.231 --> 00:34:28.065 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Another
criteria is whether or not

00:34:28.065 --> 00:34:29.333 align:middle line:90%
they have to do with death.

00:34:29.333 --> 00:34:30.835 align:middle line:84%
Carl Jung, the
great psychologist,

00:34:30.835 --> 00:34:32.570 align:middle line:84%
said that if you have
a dream about death,

00:34:32.570 --> 00:34:34.672 align:middle line:84%
you better pay attention,
because you might not

00:34:34.672 --> 00:34:36.107 align:middle line:90%
get a second chance.

00:34:36.107 --> 00:34:38.275 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Interesting-- death
of yourself, or others,

00:34:38.275 --> 00:34:39.811 align:middle line:90%
or in general?

00:34:39.811 --> 00:34:41.179 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Yes, in general.

00:34:41.179 --> 00:34:43.447 align:middle line:90%
Another is that they're shared.

00:34:43.447 --> 00:34:46.685 align:middle line:84%
A lot of people have shared
dreams with their spouse,

00:34:46.685 --> 00:34:48.652 align:middle line:84%
with their lover,
with their friends.

00:34:48.652 --> 00:34:51.856 align:middle line:84%
And if people begin to have the
same dream about some upcoming

00:34:51.856 --> 00:34:55.327 align:middle line:84%
tragedy, for example the
9/11 World Trade Center

00:34:55.327 --> 00:34:57.429 align:middle line:84%
things, which I talk
about in the book,

00:34:57.429 --> 00:35:01.066 align:middle line:84%
shared dreams are a huge
clue that you better

00:35:01.066 --> 00:35:02.334 align:middle line:90%
wake up and pay attention.

00:35:02.334 --> 00:35:03.568 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: And watch out.

00:35:03.568 --> 00:35:04.970 align:middle line:84%
Catherine from
Facebook is saying,

00:35:04.970 --> 00:35:07.505 align:middle line:84%
in my dreams I sometimes get
the feeling I'm getting messages

00:35:07.505 --> 00:35:10.275 align:middle line:84%
from people who have died,
telling me that they're OK.

00:35:10.275 --> 00:35:11.142 align:middle line:90%
Is that possible?

00:35:11.142 --> 00:35:13.278 align:middle line:84%
Is that actually a
type of premonition?

00:35:13.278 --> 00:35:15.613 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I think
it's a type of what

00:35:15.613 --> 00:35:18.083 align:middle line:84%
I want to call a non
local communication.

00:35:18.083 --> 00:35:22.854 align:middle line:84%
It doesn't seem to be a
premonition in the sense

00:35:22.854 --> 00:35:24.522 align:middle line:84%
that we've been
talking about them.

00:35:24.522 --> 00:35:26.925 align:middle line:84%
But I think that this is
a very valid phenomenon.

00:35:26.925 --> 00:35:29.060 align:middle line:90%
It occurs all the time.

00:35:29.060 --> 00:35:30.996 align:middle line:84%
And this might be an
opportunity for me

00:35:30.996 --> 00:35:34.366 align:middle line:84%
to slip in a plug
for my next book.

00:35:34.366 --> 00:35:38.036 align:middle line:84%
It's called The One Mind,
in which I make the proposal

00:35:38.036 --> 00:35:41.606 align:middle line:84%
that there is a Universal Mind
in which people communicate

00:35:41.606 --> 00:35:43.274 align:middle line:84%
with people, not
only who are alive,

00:35:43.274 --> 00:35:45.810 align:middle line:84%
but people who
are also deceased.

00:35:45.810 --> 00:35:46.478 align:middle line:90%
So--

00:35:46.478 --> 00:35:47.312 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Interesting.

00:35:47.312 --> 00:35:50.582 align:middle line:84%
So there's a whole-- that's
what the theme is through both

00:35:50.582 --> 00:35:53.918 align:middle line:84%
of your books, is the healing
words and the premonitions,

00:35:53.918 --> 00:35:55.653 align:middle line:90%
is that this is all about--

00:35:55.653 --> 00:35:57.122 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: It's
about consciousness.

00:35:57.122 --> 00:35:57.622 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: About consciousness.

00:35:57.622 --> 00:35:59.224 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: It's
about how it isn't

00:35:59.224 --> 00:36:01.092 align:middle line:90%
confined to the here and now.

00:36:01.092 --> 00:36:03.628 align:middle line:84%
And so I think that this
is a typical example

00:36:03.628 --> 00:36:04.896 align:middle line:90%
of how that manifests.

00:36:04.896 --> 00:36:06.765 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: It's about a
universal consciousness?

00:36:06.765 --> 00:36:09.300 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: A universal mind,
a universal consciousness,

00:36:09.300 --> 00:36:11.970 align:middle line:84%
what Carl Jung called the
collective unconscious--

00:36:11.970 --> 00:36:14.239 align:middle line:84%
but the idea is that you
can't put consciousness

00:36:14.239 --> 00:36:17.075 align:middle line:84%
in a box in a brain
and keep it there.

00:36:17.075 --> 00:36:19.310 align:middle line:90%
It just won't stay in the brain.

00:36:19.310 --> 00:36:21.579 align:middle line:90%
It manifests in the distance--

00:36:21.579 --> 00:36:22.247 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Outside.

00:36:22.247 --> 00:36:24.082 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: --and
outside the present.

00:36:24.082 --> 00:36:25.917 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: And that's
actually the other thing,

00:36:25.917 --> 00:36:28.720 align:middle line:84%
is we didn't get to the fifth
symptom of the premonition.

00:36:28.720 --> 00:36:30.155 align:middle line:84%
Something to look
for is that they

00:36:30.155 --> 00:36:32.891 align:middle line:84%
had to do with something
in your bodily symptoms.

00:36:32.891 --> 00:36:35.026 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Oh, bodily
symptoms-- a lot of people

00:36:35.026 --> 00:36:37.829 align:middle line:84%
who have valid premonitions,
even in dreams,

00:36:37.829 --> 00:36:40.432 align:middle line:84%
have associated
physical symptoms

00:36:40.432 --> 00:36:44.569 align:middle line:84%
at the time they're having them,
which is a hugely helpful clue.

00:36:44.569 --> 00:36:46.971 align:middle line:84%
These are not very
common, having a symptom

00:36:46.971 --> 00:36:49.274 align:middle line:84%
associated with
your premonition.

00:36:49.274 --> 00:36:51.142 align:middle line:84%
I have a friend who's
a gynecologist who

00:36:51.142 --> 00:36:54.913 align:middle line:84%
has premonitions about when his
patients are going to deliver.

00:36:54.913 --> 00:36:57.382 align:middle line:84%
This is always associated
with the feeling

00:36:57.382 --> 00:37:01.152 align:middle line:84%
of a strange sensation
in his chest.

00:37:01.152 --> 00:37:04.189 align:middle line:84%
It's so reliable that the
nurses call him up and ask him

00:37:04.189 --> 00:37:07.058 align:middle line:84%
how his chest feels when
they're uncertain when

00:37:07.058 --> 00:37:07.959 align:middle line:90%
a patient's going to--

00:37:07.959 --> 00:37:08.893 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So he knows
the baby's going

00:37:08.893 --> 00:37:10.862 align:middle line:84%
to come in when he has
this certain palpitation?

00:37:10.862 --> 00:37:13.131 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Exactly, he has
the feeling of a premonition

00:37:13.131 --> 00:37:15.867 align:middle line:84%
always associated with this very
strange feeling in his chest.

00:37:15.867 --> 00:37:16.801 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Oh my goodness.

00:37:16.801 --> 00:37:18.369 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: I know,
it's weird, isn't it?

00:37:18.369 --> 00:37:19.237 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: That's great.

00:37:19.237 --> 00:37:20.905 align:middle line:90%
So what difference do they make?

00:37:20.905 --> 00:37:22.340 align:middle line:84%
What difference
have premonitions

00:37:22.340 --> 00:37:25.643 align:middle line:90%
made in our universe?

00:37:25.643 --> 00:37:28.446 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well I think
one difference is it

00:37:28.446 --> 00:37:29.814 align:middle line:84%
that they can help
us stay alive.

00:37:29.814 --> 00:37:33.418 align:middle line:84%
I think that these things have
what evolutionary biologists

00:37:33.418 --> 00:37:35.453 align:middle line:90%
call survival value.

00:37:35.453 --> 00:37:37.222 align:middle line:90%
This is not hard to get.

00:37:37.222 --> 00:37:41.259 align:middle line:84%
If you had an ability to see
what's coming down the track,

00:37:41.259 --> 00:37:44.762 align:middle line:84%
even seconds or
minutes ahead of time,

00:37:44.762 --> 00:37:47.031 align:middle line:84%
it would give you an
opportunity to avoid life

00:37:47.031 --> 00:37:48.633 align:middle line:90%
threatening situations.

00:37:48.633 --> 00:37:54.205 align:middle line:84%
So you'd stay alive, have a
greater chance to reproduce

00:37:54.205 --> 00:37:55.406 align:middle line:90%
and perpetuate your genes.

00:37:55.406 --> 00:37:57.775 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: But can you practice it?

00:37:57.775 --> 00:37:59.244 align:middle line:90%
Can you get better at it?

00:37:59.244 --> 00:38:00.278 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Oh, absolutely.

00:38:00.278 --> 00:38:01.146 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:38:01.146 --> 00:38:01.946 align:middle line:90%
How?

00:38:01.946 --> 00:38:04.182 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Yeah, I
want to say that there

00:38:04.182 --> 00:38:07.719 align:middle line:84%
are people who are born with
huge talent in this area.

00:38:07.719 --> 00:38:10.155 align:middle line:84%
There are premonition
prodigies, like there

00:38:10.155 --> 00:38:12.357 align:middle line:84%
are prodigies in athletics,
math, music, in anything.

00:38:12.357 --> 00:38:13.591 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: We call them psychics.

00:38:13.591 --> 00:38:14.692 align:middle line:90%
We call them-- right.

00:38:14.692 --> 00:38:15.460 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Exactly.

00:38:15.460 --> 00:38:17.896 align:middle line:84%
So there are people who
are born with this gift--

00:38:17.896 --> 00:38:19.464 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Medical intuitives.

00:38:19.464 --> 00:38:21.999 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: --but if you want to
become more premonition prone

00:38:21.999 --> 00:38:25.503 align:middle line:84%
and cultivate this, there are
two especially helpful things.

00:38:25.503 --> 00:38:28.039 align:middle line:84%
One is just to
keep a dream diary

00:38:28.039 --> 00:38:31.409 align:middle line:84%
where you write down
the dream on awakening,

00:38:31.409 --> 00:38:33.378 align:middle line:84%
or talk it into a
tape recorder-- record

00:38:33.378 --> 00:38:34.779 align:middle line:90%
it in some way.

00:38:34.779 --> 00:38:38.249 align:middle line:90%
This makes them more frequent.

00:38:38.249 --> 00:38:41.719 align:middle line:84%
They are likely to happen
to you if you open up

00:38:41.719 --> 00:38:43.688 align:middle line:90%
to them by doing this ritual.

00:38:43.688 --> 00:38:46.691 align:middle line:84%
And also, perfecting a
discipline of meditation,

00:38:46.691 --> 00:38:49.360 align:middle line:84%
whether you call
it reverie, or just

00:38:49.360 --> 00:38:52.797 align:middle line:84%
time out, or getting quieter, or
formal meditation-- people who

00:38:52.797 --> 00:38:56.034 align:middle line:84%
do this have an ability
to let unconscious

00:38:56.034 --> 00:38:58.636 align:middle line:84%
processes come up
into awareness.

00:38:58.636 --> 00:39:00.605 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK, with that intention?

00:39:00.605 --> 00:39:02.273 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Yes, with
that intention.

00:39:02.273 --> 00:39:05.510 align:middle line:84%
So keeping a dream diary
and developing a disciplined

00:39:05.510 --> 00:39:07.845 align:middle line:84%
practice of meditation
are the two best ways

00:39:07.845 --> 00:39:10.114 align:middle line:84%
to becoming more
premonition prone.

00:39:10.114 --> 00:39:11.583 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So if all
of this is true,

00:39:11.583 --> 00:39:14.018 align:middle line:84%
and if the studies in
your book are all true,

00:39:14.018 --> 00:39:15.920 align:middle line:84%
and all that we're
talking about is true,

00:39:15.920 --> 00:39:22.126 align:middle line:84%
would it be fair to say that we
are definitely all connected?

00:39:22.126 --> 00:39:24.329 align:middle line:84%
And so what you
do to other people

00:39:24.329 --> 00:39:25.897 align:middle line:84%
will eventually
come back around.

00:39:25.897 --> 00:39:27.298 align:middle line:90%
Does that validate karma?

00:39:27.298 --> 00:39:29.467 align:middle line:84%
There are so many places
you can go with this.

00:39:29.467 --> 00:39:31.035 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well,
that's a beautiful way

00:39:31.035 --> 00:39:33.538 align:middle line:84%
to express what I think
is one of the key lessons

00:39:33.538 --> 00:39:35.640 align:middle line:90%
from premonitions.

00:39:35.640 --> 00:39:37.775 align:middle line:84%
I think that there's,
as you just brought

00:39:37.775 --> 00:39:39.978 align:middle line:84%
up, an ethical
dimension to this.

00:39:39.978 --> 00:39:42.113 align:middle line:84%
And it has to do with the
fact that we're connected.

00:39:44.782 --> 00:39:48.152 align:middle line:84%
I've suggested that
the reality of this,

00:39:48.152 --> 00:39:49.921 align:middle line:84%
showing that we're
all connected,

00:39:49.921 --> 00:39:54.559 align:middle line:84%
allows us to revise the
golden rule and up the ante,

00:39:54.559 --> 00:39:58.830 align:middle line:84%
as it were, by
saying that it's more

00:39:58.830 --> 00:40:03.167 align:middle line:84%
about-- it's something that
goes beyond doing something

00:40:03.167 --> 00:40:05.770 align:middle line:84%
to others because you want them
to do something nice for you,

00:40:05.770 --> 00:40:09.240 align:middle line:84%
which is the usual way the
golden rule is phrased.

00:40:09.240 --> 00:40:13.111 align:middle line:84%
We can change that to this--
be nice to other people,

00:40:13.111 --> 00:40:16.481 align:middle line:84%
because in some
sense, they are you.

00:40:16.481 --> 00:40:19.984 align:middle line:84%
And this just kind of, I
think, intensifies this idea

00:40:19.984 --> 00:40:21.819 align:middle line:90%
that we're all connected.

00:40:21.819 --> 00:40:26.591 align:middle line:84%
And we'd better be careful about
how we behave to other people.

00:40:26.591 --> 00:40:28.893 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, that
makes absolute sense.

00:40:28.893 --> 00:40:30.228 align:middle line:90%
And I'm glad that you said that.

00:40:30.228 --> 00:40:32.463 align:middle line:84%
Because there is an ethical
implication of what you're

00:40:32.463 --> 00:40:35.266 align:middle line:84%
talking about here, that
regardless of science

00:40:35.266 --> 00:40:38.269 align:middle line:84%
or whatever, it
validates that morality

00:40:38.269 --> 00:40:41.706 align:middle line:84%
of staying-- of treating
your neighbors as you would,

00:40:41.706 --> 00:40:44.208 align:middle line:84%
of course, want to
be treated yourself.

00:40:44.208 --> 00:40:45.943 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I think
that that's right.

00:40:45.943 --> 00:40:49.881 align:middle line:84%
And this also brings up
the idea of selfishness.

00:40:49.881 --> 00:40:52.650 align:middle line:84%
If you want to
develop premonitions

00:40:52.650 --> 00:40:57.622 align:middle line:84%
to say, win the lottery
or make a killing on Wall

00:40:57.622 --> 00:41:00.024 align:middle line:84%
Street and the
stock market, it's

00:41:00.024 --> 00:41:01.159 align:middle line:90%
probably not going to work.

00:41:01.159 --> 00:41:03.227 align:middle line:84%
Because the research
shows that if people

00:41:03.227 --> 00:41:07.332 align:middle line:84%
try to cultivate premonitions
because of greed,

00:41:07.332 --> 00:41:09.233 align:middle line:84%
it just messes up
the whole thing.

00:41:09.233 --> 00:41:10.768 align:middle line:90%
It just doesn't work.

00:41:10.768 --> 00:41:14.205 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So can premonitions
be used in an adverse affect?

00:41:14.205 --> 00:41:17.141 align:middle line:84%
Can you use them in a harmful
way, if this is so powerful

00:41:17.141 --> 00:41:19.944 align:middle line:90%
and if this is true?

00:41:19.944 --> 00:41:24.515 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I think that
that is an aspect of this.

00:41:24.515 --> 00:41:27.352 align:middle line:90%
And I touch on this in the book.

00:41:27.352 --> 00:41:29.520 align:middle line:84%
But I'd rather keep
our conversation

00:41:29.520 --> 00:41:31.823 align:middle line:84%
on an upbeat,
positive level here

00:41:31.823 --> 00:41:35.226 align:middle line:84%
and emphasize the way that
we can use premonitions

00:41:35.226 --> 00:41:38.963 align:middle line:84%
in a benevolent, charitable,
and compassionate way

00:41:38.963 --> 00:41:41.199 align:middle line:84%
to make the world a better
place, instead of a worse

00:41:41.199 --> 00:41:41.733 align:middle line:90%
place.

00:41:41.733 --> 00:41:43.568 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, I absolutely
agree with that.

00:41:43.568 --> 00:41:46.037 align:middle line:84%
And we did talk a little
bit offline about the fact

00:41:46.037 --> 00:41:48.339 align:middle line:84%
that the premonitions
could be used in a way

00:41:48.339 --> 00:41:53.578 align:middle line:84%
to reduce bacteria, to
shrink cancer cells--

00:41:53.578 --> 00:41:55.313 align:middle line:84%
things like that,
where they can actually

00:41:55.313 --> 00:41:58.216 align:middle line:84%
make a positive effect,
but used in an adverse way.

00:41:58.216 --> 00:42:00.752 align:middle line:84%
But it could still affect
people in a healing way.

00:42:00.752 --> 00:42:03.421 align:middle line:84%
But it always has to be done in
the name of healing, I believe.

00:42:03.421 --> 00:42:04.889 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Actually,
if premonitions

00:42:04.889 --> 00:42:07.525 align:middle line:84%
are going to work
optimally, there

00:42:07.525 --> 00:42:11.863 align:middle line:84%
has to be compassionate
intentions and a feeling

00:42:11.863 --> 00:42:17.235 align:middle line:84%
that we are connected in
almost always a loving way.

00:42:17.235 --> 00:42:20.505 align:middle line:84%
If you really want this
stuff to get off the ground

00:42:20.505 --> 00:42:24.375 align:middle line:84%
and pay dividends in
your life, then it

00:42:24.375 --> 00:42:26.978 align:middle line:84%
has to be done out of love
and compassion and a sense

00:42:26.978 --> 00:42:31.282 align:middle line:84%
that I really care about you
and you really care about me,

00:42:31.282 --> 00:42:33.317 align:middle line:84%
and there's something
like this between us.

00:42:33.317 --> 00:42:35.653 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Yep, that's what
this next slide suggests,

00:42:35.653 --> 00:42:40.224 align:middle line:84%
is that we have this single,
unitary mind in some ways.

00:42:40.224 --> 00:42:43.394 align:middle line:84%
So if you really are using
premonitions in the right way,

00:42:43.394 --> 00:42:48.499 align:middle line:84%
it goes into that single
mind of the highest

00:42:48.499 --> 00:42:51.169 align:middle line:90%
order, which is always love.

00:42:51.169 --> 00:42:53.070 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I
think that we're

00:42:53.070 --> 00:42:57.375 align:middle line:84%
faced in our world with a
lot of challenges today,

00:42:57.375 --> 00:43:01.412 align:middle line:84%
from climate change
to overpopulation,

00:43:01.412 --> 00:43:03.481 align:middle line:90%
to greed and acquisitiveness.

00:43:03.481 --> 00:43:05.716 align:middle line:84%
And if we're going to get
out of this and scrape

00:43:05.716 --> 00:43:08.686 align:middle line:84%
by as a species, I think we
better develop this sense

00:43:08.686 --> 00:43:11.189 align:middle line:84%
that we're in it together,
and that we're connected.

00:43:11.189 --> 00:43:14.592 align:middle line:84%
Otherwise, things
don't look really

00:43:14.592 --> 00:43:17.228 align:middle line:84%
well for the future
of the human race.

00:43:17.228 --> 00:43:19.864 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: That is a very good
overarching conversation

00:43:19.864 --> 00:43:21.399 align:middle line:90%
right there, absolutely.

00:43:21.399 --> 00:43:26.270 align:middle line:84%
This is something that helps
the overall human race.

00:43:26.270 --> 00:43:27.605 align:middle line:90%
Absolutely.

00:43:27.605 --> 00:43:29.841 align:middle line:84%
We have a comment
coming in from Facebook.

00:43:29.841 --> 00:43:33.978 align:middle line:84%
Barbara says that her
dad is an atheist.

00:43:33.978 --> 00:43:36.514 align:middle line:84%
And are there studies
behind premonitions?

00:43:36.514 --> 00:43:38.416 align:middle line:84%
Are there scientific
studies behind this?

00:43:38.416 --> 00:43:40.117 align:middle line:84%
We've touched on a
little bit about this.

00:43:40.117 --> 00:43:41.652 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Well, absolutely.

00:43:41.652 --> 00:43:44.655 align:middle line:84%
The studies that
I've already alluded

00:43:44.655 --> 00:43:47.024 align:middle line:84%
to that Dr. Radin and
many other investigators

00:43:47.024 --> 00:43:51.128 align:middle line:84%
have done with the
computer based studies

00:43:51.128 --> 00:43:54.065 align:middle line:84%
showing that we can know
unconsciously what's

00:43:54.065 --> 00:43:58.469 align:middle line:84%
happening-- these
experiments work

00:43:58.469 --> 00:44:01.272 align:middle line:84%
as well on agnostics
and atheists as they

00:44:01.272 --> 00:44:04.141 align:middle line:84%
do on believers in all
of this sort of thing.

00:44:04.141 --> 00:44:07.945 align:middle line:84%
So yeah, the key thing
is not whether or not

00:44:07.945 --> 00:44:09.914 align:middle line:84%
you're agnostic or
atheistic or believers.

00:44:09.914 --> 00:44:10.982 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: It doesn't matter.

00:44:10.982 --> 00:44:12.383 align:middle line:90%
It just works for everyone.

00:44:12.383 --> 00:44:12.750 align:middle line:90%
>>DOSSEY: Yeah.

00:44:12.750 --> 00:44:13.084 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: OK.

00:44:13.084 --> 00:44:15.186 align:middle line:84%
Another one from Facebook
is asking-- and thank you

00:44:15.186 --> 00:44:17.121 align:middle line:84%
for your comments coming
in-- how can women

00:44:17.121 --> 00:44:20.625 align:middle line:84%
overcome societal instincts
to be nice to strangers when

00:44:20.625 --> 00:44:24.428 align:middle line:84%
our intuition is telling us
we're in dangerous situations?

00:44:24.428 --> 00:44:27.999 align:middle line:84%
Instinct-- is there a difference
between instinct, intuition,

00:44:27.999 --> 00:44:28.900 align:middle line:90%
and premonition?

00:44:28.900 --> 00:44:32.904 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well I think you can
fiddle with the definitions.

00:44:32.904 --> 00:44:34.705 align:middle line:84%
For my part, I think
it's impossible to put

00:44:34.705 --> 00:44:36.774 align:middle line:84%
these things in a box
and separate them.

00:44:36.774 --> 00:44:39.944 align:middle line:84%
I think instinct and
premonitions, precognition

00:44:39.944 --> 00:44:43.614 align:middle line:84%
and intuition, hunches,
vibes, gut feelings--

00:44:43.614 --> 00:44:46.951 align:middle line:84%
I think all those things are
what I'm calling premonitions,

00:44:46.951 --> 00:44:50.121 align:middle line:84%
or an intuition
about the future.

00:44:50.121 --> 00:44:51.989 align:middle line:84%
I would say we just
have to be open

00:44:51.989 --> 00:44:54.692 align:middle line:90%
and trust our gut instincts.

00:44:54.692 --> 00:45:02.300 align:middle line:84%
I think when we deny the
validity of those things that

00:45:02.300 --> 00:45:04.602 align:middle line:84%
just hammer on the door
and tell us, don't do that.

00:45:04.602 --> 00:45:05.303 align:middle line:90%
Don't go there.

00:45:05.303 --> 00:45:06.938 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Right, right.

00:45:06.938 --> 00:45:08.739 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: These deserve
to be listened to.

00:45:08.739 --> 00:45:13.144 align:middle line:84%
And when we deny that, I think
it's an open door for disaster,

00:45:13.144 --> 00:45:13.678 align:middle line:90%
occasionally.

00:45:13.678 --> 00:45:15.580 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Do you think
that most people listen

00:45:15.580 --> 00:45:18.583 align:middle line:84%
to the premonitions
that are frightening,

00:45:18.583 --> 00:45:21.218 align:middle line:84%
rather than the-- have you
heard many people say, hey,

00:45:21.218 --> 00:45:22.787 align:middle line:84%
I had this premonition
I got this job.

00:45:22.787 --> 00:45:26.324 align:middle line:84%
Or I had a premonition
that I had a baby.

00:45:26.324 --> 00:45:29.493 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well the idea that
premonitions operate just

00:45:29.493 --> 00:45:32.597 align:middle line:84%
to warn us about horrible things
is not absolutely correct.

00:45:32.597 --> 00:45:34.932 align:middle line:84%
But people have intuitions
and premonitions

00:45:34.932 --> 00:45:40.638 align:middle line:84%
about nice things--
pregnancy, a job promotion,

00:45:40.638 --> 00:45:43.007 align:middle line:84%
where you're going to
meet your soul mate.

00:45:43.007 --> 00:45:44.909 align:middle line:84%
I've got a stack of
these kinds of reports

00:45:44.909 --> 00:45:48.946 align:middle line:84%
from people that deal with
positive, wonderful type

00:45:48.946 --> 00:45:50.348 align:middle line:90%
premonitions.

00:45:50.348 --> 00:45:53.084 align:middle line:84%
I even have a friend
who says that she

00:45:53.084 --> 00:45:56.087 align:middle line:84%
has an unfailing
ability to know where

00:45:56.087 --> 00:45:59.624 align:middle line:84%
the last remaining
parking spot is.

00:45:59.624 --> 00:46:00.257 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Really?

00:46:00.257 --> 00:46:01.359 align:middle line:90%
That's practical.

00:46:01.359 --> 00:46:04.061 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Yeah, practical--
and she says, interestingly,

00:46:04.061 --> 00:46:06.631 align:middle line:84%
that these premonitions
are mediated

00:46:06.631 --> 00:46:10.568 align:middle line:84%
by a goddess which
she calls Asphalta.

00:46:10.568 --> 00:46:12.203 align:middle line:90%
So Asphalta--

00:46:12.203 --> 00:46:13.904 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: This is
what she's made up?

00:46:13.904 --> 00:46:15.306 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: She says
it never fails.

00:46:15.306 --> 00:46:17.375 align:middle line:84%
And I haven't put
her to the test,

00:46:17.375 --> 00:46:19.477 align:middle line:84%
but this has caught
on in certain circles.

00:46:19.477 --> 00:46:23.147 align:middle line:84%
And on the internet you can
actually order little goddesses

00:46:23.147 --> 00:46:26.384 align:middle line:84%
now with little angel wings
that are called Asphalta.

00:46:26.384 --> 00:46:29.620 align:middle line:84%
You can hang them from
your rear view mirror,

00:46:29.620 --> 00:46:32.757 align:middle line:84%
if you're into
goddesses and Asphalta.

00:46:32.757 --> 00:46:35.092 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: Well, that's a
practical application for it.

00:46:35.092 --> 00:46:38.362 align:middle line:84%
How many other ways can we
use the idea of premonitions

00:46:38.362 --> 00:46:40.965 align:middle line:84%
in a practical way--
maybe in business.

00:46:40.965 --> 00:46:43.701 align:middle line:90%
Can we foreshadow things?

00:46:43.701 --> 00:46:46.070 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, there have
been a lot of studies looking

00:46:46.070 --> 00:46:49.106 align:middle line:84%
at the connection between
premonitions and success

00:46:49.106 --> 00:46:50.775 align:middle line:90%
in business.

00:46:50.775 --> 00:46:55.713 align:middle line:84%
As a matter of fact, a lot of
Fortune 500 corporation CEOs

00:46:55.713 --> 00:46:56.914 align:middle line:90%
have been tested.

00:46:56.914 --> 00:46:59.750 align:middle line:84%
And interestingly, the ones who
score highest on premonition

00:46:59.750 --> 00:47:02.987 align:middle line:84%
abilities are the ones
who are most successful

00:47:02.987 --> 00:47:05.289 align:middle line:84%
in the bottom lines
of their corporations.

00:47:05.289 --> 00:47:08.826 align:middle line:84%
So there's a strong correlation
between premonition ability

00:47:08.826 --> 00:47:10.628 align:middle line:90%
and success in business.

00:47:10.628 --> 00:47:13.197 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How do they score
high in premonition abilities?

00:47:13.197 --> 00:47:14.665 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: There
are tests where you

00:47:14.665 --> 00:47:18.502 align:middle line:84%
can have people predict
what number's coming up

00:47:18.502 --> 00:47:20.304 align:middle line:90%
in a string of 10 digits.

00:47:20.304 --> 00:47:21.672 align:middle line:84%
These are very
complicated tests.

00:47:21.672 --> 00:47:23.974 align:middle line:84%
But it really does
test people's ability

00:47:23.974 --> 00:47:26.544 align:middle line:84%
to see what's coming
down the pike.

00:47:26.544 --> 00:47:27.478 align:middle line:90%
But there's a warning.

00:47:27.478 --> 00:47:29.747 align:middle line:84%
And I've already touched
on it a little bit.

00:47:29.747 --> 00:47:33.117 align:middle line:84%
If people really
want to go after this

00:47:33.117 --> 00:47:38.756 align:middle line:84%
and say oh, I'm going to use my
premonitions to break the bank

00:47:38.756 --> 00:47:43.127 align:middle line:84%
or win the big lottery, it
usually just goes south.

00:47:43.127 --> 00:47:49.233 align:middle line:84%
If greed enters into your desire
to become good at premonitions,

00:47:49.233 --> 00:47:52.236 align:middle line:84%
you can predict that that's
not going to work very well.

00:47:52.236 --> 00:47:54.572 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: So this wasn't a
premonition of you, of yours,

00:47:54.572 --> 00:47:55.673 align:middle line:90%
to write this book, right?

00:47:55.673 --> 00:47:57.975 align:middle line:84%
You kind of backed
into this whole thing.

00:47:57.975 --> 00:47:59.677 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Yeah, I
didn't want to do this.

00:47:59.677 --> 00:48:00.878 align:middle line:90%
But I--

00:48:00.878 --> 00:48:02.880 align:middle line:84%
>>LISA: How has it
been received when

00:48:02.880 --> 00:48:04.815 align:middle line:84%
you go to medical
communities and you

00:48:04.815 --> 00:48:06.217 align:middle line:90%
lecture about premonitions?

00:48:06.217 --> 00:48:07.752 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Well, I
had the opportunity

00:48:07.752 --> 00:48:10.755 align:middle line:84%
to put that to the test
a couple years ago,

00:48:10.755 --> 00:48:16.627 align:middle line:84%
talking to a large group of
Harvard-affiliated doctors

00:48:16.627 --> 00:48:20.231 align:middle line:84%
who were gathered for a
continuing medical education

00:48:20.231 --> 00:48:21.398 align:middle line:90%
course in internal medicine.

00:48:21.398 --> 00:48:23.434 align:middle line:84%
They wanted me to talk
about something different,

00:48:23.434 --> 00:48:25.703 align:middle line:84%
so I thought I'd talk about
premonitions, expecting

00:48:25.703 --> 00:48:27.605 align:middle line:84%
that they would all
get up and walk out.

00:48:27.605 --> 00:48:28.773 align:middle line:90%
Nobody left.

00:48:28.773 --> 00:48:31.175 align:middle line:84%
And in the Q&A
session, for example,

00:48:31.175 --> 00:48:33.611 align:middle line:84%
they began to tell me
their premonitions.

00:48:33.611 --> 00:48:36.714 align:middle line:84%
One female intern stood
up and she said, well

00:48:36.714 --> 00:48:38.282 align:middle line:90%
I get premonitions.

00:48:38.282 --> 00:48:40.918 align:middle line:90%
I get numbers in my dreams.

00:48:40.918 --> 00:48:45.022 align:middle line:84%
She said, I dream the specific
values of my patients' lab

00:48:45.022 --> 00:48:48.092 align:middle line:84%
tests before I even
order the tests.

00:48:48.092 --> 00:48:49.393 align:middle line:90%
And it went from there.

00:48:49.393 --> 00:48:50.194 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Wow.

00:48:50.194 --> 00:48:50.795 align:middle line:90%
Oh, really?

00:48:50.795 --> 00:48:51.996 align:middle line:90%
And more people--

00:48:51.996 --> 00:48:54.165 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: Yeah, people
just came forward,

00:48:54.165 --> 00:48:56.700 align:middle line:84%
as if I gave them premonitions,
for the first time

00:48:56.700 --> 00:48:59.103 align:middle line:84%
in their life, to go
public with this stuff.

00:48:59.103 --> 00:48:59.904 align:middle line:90%
And many of them--

00:48:59.904 --> 00:49:00.137 align:middle line:90%
>>LISA: Gave them permission.

00:49:00.137 --> 00:49:02.540 align:middle line:84%
>>DOSSEY: --would introduce
their comments by saying,

00:49:02.540 --> 00:49:03.874 align:middle line:90%
